The Premier League (legal name: The Football Association Premier League Limited) is the highest level of the English football league system. Contested by 20 clubs, it operates on a system of promotion and relegation with the English Football League (EFL). Seasons typically run from August to May with each team playing 38 matches (playing all other teams both home and away). Most games are played on Saturday and Sunday afternoons, with occasional weekday evening fixtures.

The competition was founded as the FA Premier League on 20 February 1992 following the decision of clubs in the Football League First Division to break away from the Football League founded in 1888; however, teams may still be relegated into and promoted from the EFL Championship. The Premier League takes advantage of a lucrative television rights sale to Sky: from 2019 to 2020, the league's accumulated television rights deals were worth around £3.1 billion a year, with Sky and BT Group securing the domestic rights to broadcast 128 and 32 games respectively. input: What is a spatial network?
output:
it is a network of interactions among individuals that occur at the same place and time. This is a complex, dynamic, and heterogeneous network that interacts with the environment and develops according to environmental and social circumstances. The network derives from socialization, as well as from the emergence of social ties, and is influenced by the physical conditions of the place, including the dwelling characteristics, the infrastructures, and the availability of natural resources.

A spatial network is a network of interactions among individuals that occur at the same place and time.

Spatial networks can be analyzed using network theory. The basic elements of a network are individuals or places. Some of these individuals or places are connected to each other by means of relationships: they are related either by a physical proximity (through proximity networks) or by some kind of interaction (through interaction networks). The quantity of relationships between individuals or places is called the degree of the element. In a social network, the degree of each node is proportional to the number of relationships established by it. In a spatial network, the degree of each node is proportional to the number of relations that node can establish with other nodes.

Spatial networks can be analyzed using network theory. The basic elements of a network are individuals or places. Some of these individuals or places are connected to each other by means of relationships: they are related either by a physical proximity (through proximity networks) or by some kind of interaction (through interaction networks). The quantity of relationships between individuals or places is called the degree of the element. In a social network, the degree of each node is proportional to the number of relationships established by it. In a spatial network, the degree of each node is proportional to the number of relations that node can establish with other nodes.

We analyzed the spatial network of the main cities in Mexico that, according to the 2013 IPC census, have more than a million inhabitants. The degree of each node is proportional to the number of relations that node can establish with other nodes. Thus, we can distinguish a core, which is the set of nodes that have the highest number of relations with the other nodes. The leafs (or leaves) are the set of nodes that have the highest number of connections with the nodes in the core. The leaves are the most densely connected places in the network and they are the most central. We can also distinguish an intermediate region (the core of the network). Nodes that belong to the core of the network are the most central places of the network.
label: A spatial network (sometimes also geometric graph) is a graph in which the vertices or edges are spatial elements associated with geometric objects, i.e., the nodes are located in a space equipped with a certain metric. The simplest mathematical realization of spatial network is a lattice or a random geometric graph (see figure in the right), where nodes are distributed uniformly at random over a two-dimensional plane; a pair of nodes are connected if the Euclidean distance is smaller than a given neighborhood radius. Transportation and mobility networks, Internet, mobile phone networks, power grids, social and contact networks and biological neural networks are all examples where the underlying space is relevant and where the graph's topology alone does not contain all the information. Characterizing and understanding the structure, resilience and the evolution of spatial networks is crucial for many different fields ranging from urbanism to epidemiology.

Did You Know?

The word magnet is derived from the Greek word "magnes" which means "iron". Magnets are created when a type of iron called ferromagnetism is present. The iron atoms are aligned and attract one another.

What are Magnets Used For?

One of the most important applications of magnets is in the manufacture of electrical devices. Magnets are used to make the electrical connections in motors, transformers, and generators. Magnets are also used in television sets and radios. Magnets are also found in a variety of household items such as paper clips, compasses, and the lid of a medicine bottle.

A magnet is an object, composed of two plates of different metals, which are polar in nature. This means that they are attracted to one another when placed in the same direction. When placed in opposite directions, they repel. For example, iron and steel are polar.

A magnet is attracted to iron because iron has a magnetic field. A magnet is repelled from iron because iron has a non-magnetic field. Iron has a magnetic field because most of the iron atoms are aligned in the same direction.

What is the History of Magnets?

The discovery of the magnetic field began with the Greek scientist, Thales, who is believed to have been the first person to use magnets in a practical way. He used magnets to hold together the pieces of a sundial.

Magnetism was also known to the ancient Chinese. It is believed that the Chinese used magnets in the first wheel of a cart to assist in guiding the cart.

The Greeks and the Chinese also wrote about magnetism. However, the first book that was published on the subject of magnetism was by the English scientist, Michael Faraday, in 1831.

I’ve found that almond milk can be used as a dairy-free alternative in a number of recipes. You can make it with water or use the recipe below.

1 cup almonds

1/2 cup water

1/4 cup coconut sugar

1/4 cup sunflower seeds

1 tbsp almond butter

1 tsp vanilla extract

Soak the almonds in the water overnight, or for at least 6 hours, or for about 8 hours if you can.

Drain the almonds and grind them in a blender or food processor until they’re very finely ground. Add the sugar, seeds, and almond butter and blend to make a thick paste.

Transfer the paste to a bowl and mix in the vanilla.

1 banana

2 heaped tbsp rolled oats

1/2 cup chopped frozen berries

Dash of sea salt

output:
.

Madonna: It was a completely different time, and it was a time that I treasured, and when I first started, I was very much influenced by the art world, and I was very much influenced by other artists in the art world. I was very much a part of that whole, and I got to know many artists like Andy Warhol and Keith Haring. I was also very much influenced by the New York City art scene and the music scene in New York City, and I was very much influenced by the artists and musicians that were there. So that was a lot of the sense of who I was. I didn't have a choice on the music side of things, I had to do what I couldn't do in the art world. I didn't have a choice of what I wanted to do. I knew what I wanted to do, but it was very difficult for me to do in the art world, whereas in music I could just do what I wanted to do. I was very lucky to have that freedom.

What kind of an impact did Madonna have on the music scene when she first hit the scene in 1984?

Madonna: She was a great influence on the music scene, because she was so fresh, and so new, and so different. And she had this whole concept of music and what it meant to her, and her son had died and that was a very personal thing. I think it was an extremely difficult time for her, so I think she was in a lot of pain, I think she felt like she had to find something that would help her make it through that period of time. So I think she started her career with that kind of attitude, and she put a lot of herself into her music. She was a very strong woman, and she felt like she didn't have any options, and she was a woman in a man's world. So she used that to inspire herself and used that as a strength.

Reliability - The thing about being on only a single piece of equipment is that your balance relies much more on the snow conditions. Under ideal conditions, its great to be able to snowboard and maintain control with the edge. Skiing on powder is also a dream. However, if the conditions are less than ideal, then snowboarding on ice becomes a dangerous, out of control situation. Skiing on ice is also no picnic, but at least you can stabilize and balance on your two skis. 

Expediency - Skiing with friends inevitably means that you are waiting for the slowest one before you can start down the mountain. I was that friend. Snowboarders have to sit down and strap in, while skiers can pretty much get right off the lift and start down the mountain immediately.

input: What is Lean manufacturing
output:
?

Lean manufacturing is a manufacturing process, which is a set of processes that help a business to work more efficiently while also creating a higher quality product.

Lean manufacturing is an attempt to improve the quality of manufacturing processes by eliminating waste and unnecessary steps.

In the manufacturing industry, it is widely known that waste is the biggest cause of workplace accidents and also a major reason for the loss of productivity.

The aim of Lean manufacturing is to eliminate waste and also create a continuous flow of good quality products.

In Lean manufacturing, the key focus is to eliminate waste at each stage of the process by adopting a set of measures to do so.

In this process, raw materials go through a sequence of processes, which are planned to remove any unnecessary steps.

These steps are further divided into two types, which are the waste elimination and waste minimization.

The Start-up of Lean manufacturing

The start of the Lean manufacturing process was initiated by Toyota. The company started implementing the process in the mid-1980s. The process was then adopted by the other companies, and formed into a standard.

Since then, it has been adapted by many other industries, and the implementation of Lean Manufacturing has become a standard procedure.

The advantage of Lean manufacturing

The major advantage of Lean manufacturing is that it helps a company to improve its quality, efficiency, and also increase the productivity of the company.

It is a process that is designed for a particular product, which is the most important aspect of the Lean Manufacturing.

It improves the quality of the product by eliminating waste and thus, it improves the quality of the product.

The other major benefit of implementing Lean manufacturing is that it increases the productivity of the company.

The reduced time to make the product allows the company to make more products in a shorter period of time.

The reduced time also allows the company to reduce the costs of the products.

The reduced cost of the products allows the company to make the product at a lower price.

This allows the company to increase the sales of the product, and also helps in increasing the profit of the company.

It also reduces the time that it takes to market the product to the consumers, and also the time that it takes to deliver the product to the consumers.

input: Where can I go to request an absentee ballot for an upcoming election in Wisconsin, or to track the status of my ballot request?
output:
online: http://www.vote.wi.gov/elections/vote/absentee-ballots/

How does the absentee voting process work in Wisconsin?

To request an absentee ballot, you must apply in-person at your local polling place between 8 a.m. and 8 p.m. on Election Day. You can download the application and return it in person at the same time you request your ballot or you can mail it in.

If I apply for an absentee ballot online, can I request it the same day I apply in person?

No. You can request your ballot online at any time before the election. There is no guarantee you will receive your ballot on Election Day.

If I apply for an absentee ballot in person, can I apply online for my ballot?

Yes. If you have applied online in-person, you can apply for your ballot online.

If I apply for an absentee ballot by mail, can I request it the same day I apply in person?

No. Absentee ballots are mailed to all qualified applicants no later than seven days prior to Election Day.

If I request an absentee ballot, how will it be delivered?

You will receive a ballot in the mail. The ballot will be sent to the address we have on file for you. If you or your spouse do not receive your ballot by Election Day, you should contact your local election official.

How do I know if my absentee ballot request was received by the Board of Elections?

Your ballot request will be sent to the Board of Elections. We will send you a notice if your ballot request is received by the Board of Elections.

How do I know if my absentee ballot request was received by the Board of Elections?

Your ballot request will be sent to the Board of Elections. We will send you a notice if your ballot request is received by the Board of Elections.

How long will my absentee ballot request be processed by the Board of Elections?

You can request your ballot up to 24 hours before Election Day. If you do not receive your ballot in the mail, your absentee ballot request was received by the Board of Elections.

How do I know if my absentee ballot request was received by the Board of Elections?

Your ballot request will be sent to the Board of Elections.

The woman was taken to the hospital for treatment. The dog was not located.

EtymologyIn 1798, a Group of bees at Cambridge University, under the leadership of John Stevens Henslow, with the help of naturalist William Ayrton, discovered the pollen-collecting habits of bumblebees. The word bumblebee derived from the first letters of their names, though "bumble", the common term for bumblebees, came later, probably after the species of bumblebee was named.

Origin and distributionBumblebees are common in the British Isles and on many of the surrounding islands, including the Isle of Man, the Channel Islands, the Isle of Wight, the Isle of Arran, the Lizard Peninsula, the Orkney Islands, Shetland, and the Hebrides. The species, however, is absent from the Hebrides and the Outer Hebrides.

DescriptionBumblebees are relatively small insects, with a body length of approximately 2 cm (0.8 in.), a width of approximately 0.8 cm (0.33 in.), and a wingspan of approximately 0.5 cm (0.2 in.). The body is covered in hair, and the antennae are quite short. Bumblebees have three pairs of legs. Their forewings are slender and compressed, and their hindwings are very long and narrow. Bumblebees are generally yellow or black, and their coloration is often varied, with some species being reddish, or greenish, or blue.

Bumblebees have a stinger, which is located in the abdomen at the end of the hindlegs. The stinger contains a poison called venom. Bumblebees are capable of delivering this venom to their prey by forming a tube, called a bumblebee sting, into which the venom is injected. Bumblebees do not sting people, but they do sting other insects, or their own larvae. The sting of a bumblebee is usually painful, but it is rarely fatal, and bumblebee stings are also usually not life-threatening in small children or the elderly.

Ecology and behaviorBumblebees are found in a wide variety of habitats, including urban environments, woodlands, scrub, gardens, and fields. When I was a kid, I had an orange-shaped, plastic-covered, plastic-framed, plastic-buttoned, plastic-flapped, plastic-snapped, plastic-screwed, plastic-lanced, plastic-rubbed, and plastic-screwed-in portable transistor radio. The plastic buttons for volume control were easy to replace and had the advantage of being short and easily accessible. A few years ago I visited a friend at his University campus. He had a radio that looked very similar to mine. I asked him how it worked and he told me that it was manufactured by a company called Philips. I asked him how he got it and he told me that he purchased it from a department store. I could not imagine why he would purchase it from a department store. I had no idea what a department store was and I assumed that it was a place where I would go to buy many different things that I could not afford to buy. A few years later, I learned that a department store is a store that sells clothing and other items as well as toiletries. I used to go to a department store once every two weeks and often bought all the toiletries that I needed. I had to think about it for a while to figure out why I had purchased my radio from a department store.

In the 1970s, I had a friend who worked in a factory that made plastic buttons for radios. My friend was mad at me because I was not going to buy one of his radios. I told him that I would buy it anyway because he earned it. I found a factory that manufactured the plastic buttons for radios and bought some from them. My friend was upset. input: What should I consider before taking a job with a lot of travel?
output:
, and work/life balance?

A:

Take it in context.
Is it a one time deal (ie. a contract assignment)? Or is it an ongoing consulting project that you expect to be doing for the next few years?
If it's just a one time deal, then you may find that you would be much happier working for a company within your own country (or a few hundred miles away). So you might not mind the travel, and it may be a good opportunity for you.
If however, you expect to be working with a company for a while, then maybe you should look at some of the other questions here that talk about the long term prospects for a career.
I find that there are some great opportunities for people who are willing to travel. I think that once you've worked in a few places and know what you can do, then you can make a great case for yourself.
Once you've been in a few places, then you can start with the company you want to work for and try to make a case for yourself, in your own way. The more your case can stand on its own, the more likely it is to be accepted.

A:

I am a firm believer in working abroad. I have worked for 3 companies in the past few years and am currently employed at a company that is based in a country that I have never visited.
The main reason I have found for this is to gain experience, to have more work and to get away from the routine and expectations of a home country.
If you are under the age of 30, I would recommend visiting the country you are going to if you can. If you are older, then it is more difficult to gain experience but it is possible. 
A few things to consider:

How much you want to travel.
How much you want to spend on living expenses.
How much you want to invest in a new car.
How much you are willing to learn a new language.

If you have a choice, I would recommend putting together a budget and a list of things you want to do. Then do both of these things before you leave.
My first short trip was to Thailand. I traveled for 5 days and spent $50-75 USD/day (including travel and food). I used my saved up money and bought a car. I would recommend this as a way to get away from the routine. 
If you are going to go
label: Many people are attracted to jobs that have significant travel.  The allure of traveling to new and exciting places, the potential for airline and hotel program status benefits, meeting new people, etc.  All of these things may be exactly what you are looking for.  But my advice for anyone who is considering a position with significant travel and who has not experienced that type of work-life before is to think about all the things in their life that they are involved with that make them happy.  Think hard about whether you can take them on the road with you, reproduce them wherever your business travel takes you, or do without them.  Perhaps you have a standing poker night each month with your friends.  You may not be able to attend that with any regularity.  You may love the climbing gym or cycling club at home. input: Given this paragraph about Thanjavur paintings and its origins, what are the typical features of Thanjavur paintings?
output:
Answer

Horses represent the power of the ruler. The Chola king, who was a warrior, had a horse in his court. Hence, horses appear many times in the Chola paintings.

A mare is the symbol of a queen or the deity, such as goddess. She is represented by a deer.

The Chola kings are depicted as enthroned on a horse. The king has a lion in front of him. The Chola kings were called by the Tamil word “Kulam”, which means lion. Hence, the king was depicted with a lion in the Chola paintings.

The kings of the Chola dynasty, such as Rajaraja and his son Rajendra, are depicted as sitting on horses.

The Chola kings are shown wearing a crown. The kings wore a crown to show they were the king.

The Chola kings are often shown with a flag or banner. The flag, which is a symbol of authority, was carried by the Chola kings.

In the Chola paintings, the Chola kings are shown riding a horse. Hence, India is the horse. India is depicted riding a bull.

The Chola kings are depicted on a chariot. The Chola kings were warriors. Hence, the chariot is used to show that the king was a warrior.

Other horses are also shown in the Chola paintings. The Chola kings rode horses as well as the vanquished enemies.

At present, paper and other sheet products are tested in a number of ways. For example, a sheet of paper may be folded, stuck on a piece of card, and the resulting stack of folded sheets or cards may be manually inspected. Alternatively, a sheet of paper may be inspected by an optical scanner, and the resulting image may be visually inspected or the image may be analyzed using a computer. However, the manual methods of inspection are time consuming and the optical scanners are expensive.
U.S. Pat. No. 5,091,325 discloses an apparatus for testing the quality of sheet products that is capable of automatically inspecting the quality of a sheet of paper. The apparatus disclosed in U.S. Pat. No. 5,091,325 includes a sheet handling apparatus for feeding a sheet of paper into engagement with a pair of sensors which are movable back and forth along a pair of parallel paths. The sensors are adapted to detect and analyze image information obtained by scanning a sheet of paper placed between the sensors. Each sensor produces a signal indicating the quality of the sheet of paper detected by the sensor. The signals are compared, and the result of the comparison is used to determine whether the sheet of paper is of acceptable quality.
Although the apparatus disclosed in U.S. Pat. No. 5,091,325 is capable of automatically inspecting the quality of a sheet of paper, the apparatus requires that the sheet of paper be scanned using optical scanners. The use of optical scanners increases the cost of the apparatus.
Accordingly, it is an object of the invention to provide an apparatus and method of testing the quality of a product that is capable of automatically inspecting the quality of a sheet of paper or the like without the use of optical scanners.

$ ls -l file
-rw-r--r--   1 spazzonic  staff  37788 Aug  5 05:55 file

A:

If you want to know the size of a file in one command, you can use du, in combination with --apparent-size.
This will report a size of the file, but it does not take into account what it really takes up on the filesystem.
$ du -sh file
28K file

$ du --apparent-size file
28K file

Note that this will not work with the -a option, which will report the size of the files, including hidden files.
$ du -sh file
28K file

$ du --apparent-size -a file
28K file

"It's by the laws of nature. The biggest bird has the biggest wingspan, the biggest bones, the biggest heart, and it's not as quick as the other birds. So that's why it flies farther."

An oil is a chemical substance that is composed primarily of hydrocarbons and may be animal, vegetable or petrochemical in origin.
Oil is used in a wide range of applications and is essential to everyday human life. These are:
Cooking - edible vegetable and animal oils are used for various purposes in cooking and food preparation
Cosmetics - most facial cleansers, lotions and hair care products contain molecules that come from mineral and vegetable oils
Fuel - crude oil is refined and converted to diesel, gasoline or jet fuel to power cars, trucks and planes
Heating - petrochemical oil is used for heating
Painting - oil is used as a supporting medium for paints
Lubrication - oils are used in various engineering purposes as they do not easily adhere to other substance which makes them useful as lubricants
Religion - oil has been used throughout history as a religious medium. It is often considered a spiritually purifying agent and is used to anointing purposes
Health - oils holds lots of fats and medical properties, for example fish oil holds the omega-3 fatty acid which helps with inflammation and reduces fat in the bloodstream

In order to make the right choice, it is important to understand the differences between the various types of headphones.

The three main categories of headphones are closed-back, open-back and over-ear.

Closed-back headphones totally seal off the ear canal and the ear, so all the sound is directed back into the headphones. This helps to minimise hearing loss in the long run.

Open-back headphones do not completely seal off the ear, but only partially block out some of the sound. This type of headphones can help with hearing loss, but is not recommended for prolonged listening.

Over-ear headphones completely cover the ear and seal off the ear canal. This helps to reduce ambient noise and makes it easier to hear yourself when you are on the phone or in a noisy environment.

Most people find these headphones to be uncomfortable to wear for long periods. This is because they make it uncomfortable to have a conversation with someone who is nearby, and because they are also heavy and hot.

Some people like to have their headphones with them when they are on the move, but they can cause a great deal of damage to your ears if you are listening to music for long periods of time.

On the other hand, many people find that they are not comfortable wearing headphones when they are sitting down, watching TV, or reading.

The main reason for this is that they make it difficult to hear what is going on around you.

It was designed, developed and deployed by the Institute for Development and Research in Banking Technology (IDRBT) in 2004, with the goal of inter-connecting the ATMs in the country and facilitating convenience banking. It is run by the National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI). As on 31st January’ 22, there were 1,203 members that includes 111 Direct, 1,045 Sub members, 43 RRBs and 4 WLAOs using NFS network connected to more than 2.55 Lac ATM (including cash deposit machines/recyclers).
The National Financial Switch was launched by the IDRBT on 27 August 2004, connecting the ATMs of three banks, Corporation Bank, Bank of Baroda and ICICI Bank.The IDRBT then worked towards bringing all major banks in India on board and by December 2009, the network had grown to connect 49,880 ATMs of 37 banks, thereby emerging as the largest network of shared ATMs in the country.

The 29-year-old man told police he was walking down the street when he was approached by a man he knows.

Rideau-Vanier ward Coun. Mathieu Fleury said he thinks the incident is isolated.

. It’s not TV that’s hurting kids, it’s the lack of family time that’s hurting kids. I used to be a fan of the TV-less house. But then I realized that it’s more important to spend our time together, playing, talking, and just being together. Now I can’t imagine our life without TV. I also am the first to admit that there are some shows that I would never get rid of, but those shows aren’t hurting me or my kids. I just have a hard time watching them. I’m sure you have a few shows that you watch that you wouldn’t get rid of, but maybe we can all agree to put those shows on hold until we have dinner or until after the kids go to bed.

I’m not saying we’re going to stop having time together. But maybe we can start re-evaluating how much time we’re all spending with our kids. I don’t know about you, but I would rather be playing with them then watching them play.

input: What makes a Korean corn dog different from an American corn dog?
output:
.comShopping for Korean corn dogs in the states is not easy. There are few stores carrying them, and even when they are available, the selection is limited. Even in Korea, the selection is limited. In Korea, corn dogs are not a national food, they are a regional food. They were invented by the Americans. They were a part of the American military culture. The Americans started serving them to their troops in the Korean War. They are served at the same time as fries, and every time I go to the Korean War Memorial, I stop at the hot dog stand and get a corn dog.

While most of the corn dogs served in the US are hot dogs, there is a wide variety of types. One of the most popular is the grilled corn dog, which is a grilled hot dog wrapped in a corn dog dough. The dough is made out of flour, water, and corn starch. It is rather sticky, so it takes some time to wrap the hot dog.

While Korean hot dogs are grilled, the typical American hot dog is boiled. (The hot dog vendors in Seoul boil their dogs in a large pot of boiling water.)

Korean hot dogs are also served with various toppings. I like the spicy mustard, but I have also tried the kimchi. Some people like the black bean sauce.

While it is possible to find Korean corn dogs at a few restaurants in the US, they are not widely available. Some of the best corn dogs I have eaten were at the Corn Dog Stand in Cleveland, Ohio.

For my first visit to Korea, I wanted to try one of the corn dogs from the Korean War Memorial. I was surprised to find that the Memorial was open only on the weekends. I am not sure when the Memorial reopens, but I am going to check it out on a weekend when it is not crowded.

If you are in Seoul and want to get a corn dog, here is the address:

The Memorial is open from 10 am to 5 pm on the following dates: May 15 to June 14, July 11 to August 14, September 13 to October 12, and November 10 to December 9.

San Francisco's Fillmore District

The Fillmore District is a neighborhood in the South of Market area of San Francisco, California, located between Mission and Potrero Hill. It is roughly bounded on the north by Hayes Valley, on the west by the Port of San Francisco, and on the south by the Transbay Terminal. It extends from San Francisco's Civic Center to Golden Gate Park in the east and Mission Street to the Fillmore District in the west.

The Fillmore District was first referred to as "SOMA", an abbreviation of San Francisco's Mission and Ocean Park neighborhoods. In the late 1960s and early 1970s, the neighborhood was a haven for artists and alternative subcultures, with the likes of CBGB and Throb Records. It became a center of the San Francisco punk rock movement, and was the scene of many concerts by bands such as The Ramones, The Dead Boys, The Cramps, X, The Mumps, and The Vibrators.

ear (Hobo) is a series of books written by Gertrude Chandler Warner and published by Twayne, a division of Macmillan Publishing Company, for children. The series was originally published from 1940 to 1953; Warner re-published the first three titles in the series in 1996. The publisher is now Macmillan Children's Publishing Group.

The first book in the series was published in 1940, and the series was aimed at children between the ages of eight and twelve.  Later titles were aimed at children aged six and up, and the series aimed to teach children how to count, read, write, and spell.

Early series
Gertrude Chandler Warner wrote the series under the pseudonym "Hobo", and also wrote under the pseudonym "Hobo" the previously uncollected stories "Buster's Spree" and "Buster's New York".

Warner also wrote under the pseudonym "Hobo" the novels Ginger Pye and The Secret of the Old Clock and the booklet for the series The Story of the Wizard of Oz, published in 1939.

List of series
The following is an alphabetical list of the titles of the books in the series.

Series 1
 Title: The Little House
 Inspired by the life of the author's mother, Gertrude Chandler Warner, the novel covers the entire series with the early years of the author's life. The protagonist, Marion, is a tomboy in the series, and her mother is the only person to ever call her "Marion" instead of "Mary." This book was the first in the series.
 Publisher: Twayne Publishers
 Year Published: 1940

Series 2
 Title: A Little House in the Woods
 This book covers Marion's final years at the end of the series. It is the only book in the series that does not feature Marion and her friends.
 Publisher: Twayne Publishers
 Year Published: 1941

Series 3
 Title: The Cowboy and the Little House
 This book covers Marion's life when she lived in Kansas, with her parents and brother. This book was the first book in the series to feature Marion's brother, Sam.
 Publisher: Twayne Publishers
 Year Published: 1942

Series 4
 Title: The Red House
 This book covers Marion's life while she lived in Missouri. It was the first book in the series to feature her father, John.

The Barkley Marathons is a series of running events around the world, and in the United States, that aim to raise money and awareness for the Leukemia & Lymphoma Society, and the Sickle Cell Disease and Allied Disorders Association, two of the largest organizations dedicated to the study, treatment and cure of blood diseases. Each event is named after the late Dr. James B. Barkley, a leukemia surgeon and one of the founding members of the Blood Center, who served as its first president. Over the course of the events, thousands of runners run across the country, all to raise money and awareness for the organizations that Dr. Barkley helped to found.

The Barkley Marathons began in New York City in 1987, and have since spread to other locations around the world. The Marathons are held in the spring and fall of each year, and are broken down into shorter events throughout the year. The Marathons are run exclusively on public roads. A number of the races include a race walk, which is a race in which participants run in a manner similar to a marathon, but walk at a speed which is less than the average pace of a marathon. The walk portion of the race is for charity, and generally funds the charity in question.

History
The first Barkley Marathons was held in 1987 in New York City. The first running event was held in a park near the Leukemia & Lymphoma Society's headquarters. The event was named in honor of Dr. James B. Barkley, a leukemia surgeon and the founding member of the Leukaemia Research Fund, who served as the first president of the organization. It became a yearly event in 1988, and has since grown to be one of the largest events of its kind.

In January 2015, the Barkley Marathons held its 50th running. The Marathons were held in New York, New Jersey, and Connecticut.

In the United States, the Barkley Marathons are usually held in the spring or fall. The first Barkley was held in April 1987, and the first running event to feature a walk was held in August of the same year. Since the inaugural event, the Marathons have been held in New York City, New Jersey, and Connecticut.

The Barkley Marathons have been held in other countries as well. The first events to occur in other countries have been held in Austria in 1987, and Australia in 1990.

**4. Don't think in terms of a single food, think in terms of a meal.**

The best way to count carbs is to think of a meal. Think of a plateful of pasta, pasta with tomato sauce, or a plateful of pasta with a little bit of tomato sauce and some cheese. Anything that's not a single food can be part of a meal. For example, if you eat a slice of toast with jam on it, then you have eaten a small amount of fruit, which is fine. To work out the number of carbs from the other foods in the meal, add them all up together.

**5. If you're really worried, use a food diary.**

If you have a food diary, write down everything you eat. It's the only way to accurately work out your total carb intake. If you really, really want to get to grips with counting carbs, though, a food diary is not the way to do it. A food diary will only give you the illusion of accuracy.

Pricing models are a means to calculate the price of software. They are designed to help companies provide software at competitive prices, while also making sure that the company is making a profit.

There are two main types of pricing models:

  *  **Cost center pricing model** : This pricing model is used when the software is installed and used by a specific department within the organization. In this model, the cost of the software is allocated to a particular department based on the usage of the software and the amount of money that department is responsible for. For example, a department's cost of software usage is calculated by multiplying the number of hours that the department uses the software by the cost of the software license.

  *  **Per-user pricing model** : This model is used when the software is used by multiple users. In this model, the software is licensed for each user in the organization. The cost is calculated based on the number of users and the usage of the software.

There are many types of software pricing models, but broadly they can be divided into three categories: perpetual, subscription, and consumption.

Perpetual software pricing models, also known as perpetual licensing models, allow the software to be purchased for a one-time fee.  Typically the buyer has nearly unlimited use of the software in perpetuity.  If updates to the software are required, a separate software maintenance package may be purchased.

Subscription software allows unlimited use of the software for a predetermined period, often 1 year or 3 years, for a price.  Updates to the software are often included in the price of the subscription.  At the end of the subscription term, the buyer usually has the option to renew their subscription.

Consumption-based software allows the buyer to pay for their actual usage of the software during a period of time, for example monthly.  In this type of arrangement, the actual usage can vary from period to period, resulting in customer charges that vary as well.  Some customers like knowing that they will only pay for what they use, while other customers dislike the unpredictability of their bills.

input: Why is the Pacific ocean typically cold off of the West Coast of the United States?
label:
The primary ocean current along the West Coast of the United States is often referred to as the "California Current" and follows a clockwise pattern, bringing cold water from the Gulf of Alaska southeasterly, where it eventually meets the beaches of Washington, Oregon and California.
The further south you go typically the warmer it gets so while surfers may be out in a thick wetsuit in June in San Francisco you may well see surfers and swimmers from Santa Barbara southward in shorts or a spring suit.

With the goal of clarifying the causes of climate change, NASA, the European Space Agency, the Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency, the Canadian Space Agency, and the Scientific and Technical Research Council of Spain are jointly operating the Atmospheric Composition and Climate Model Intercomparison Project (AM2I, pronounced “AM-2-ee”), which will run from Sept. 1 through March 31, 2008, at NASA’s Goddard Space Flight Center in Greenbelt, Md.

The project involves a number of high resolution and state-of-the-art Earth-based and space-based observation systems that will provide information on the composition and state of the atmosphere and climate, including:

The Atmospheric Chemistry Experiment (ACE), which will measure the abundance and distribution of ozone and other molecules in the atmosphere. ACE also will measure trace gases such as carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide and methane.

The Cloud-Aerosol Transport System (CATS), which will measure the properties of clouds and aerosols, including their size, shape, and optical properties.

The Tropospheric Emissions: Monitoring of Pollution (TEMPO), which will measure aerosol, ozone and methane concentrations, and their spatial and temporal variations.

The Polar Aerosol and Gas Experiment (PAGES), which will measure the chemical composition and size distribution of particles in polar regions.

The Airborne Laboratory for the Study of the Earth’s Atmosphere (ALMA), which will measure atmospheric composition and temperature profiles in the lower atmosphere.

The International Satellite Cloud Climatology Project (ISCCP), which will provide global observations of clouds and their effect on climate.

The Carbon Dioxide Information Analysis Center (CDIAC) in Boulder, Colo., will measure the amount of carbon dioxide in Earth’s atmosphere.

The Global Precipitation Measurement (GPM) mission, scheduled for launch in 2009, will measure the amount, type, and timing of rain and snow, and will provide the first global measurements of rainfall from space.

The Global Ozone Monitoring Experiment (GOME) in Antarctica will monitor ozone and global atmospheric properties.

Greenhouse gases in the atmosphere trap the heat from the sun and lead to an overall increase in temperature on the planet. Greenhouse gases are mostly produced by burning fossil fuels like coal, oil, and natural gas. Deforestation is also a contributing factor to global warming since trees capture carbon from the atmosphere when growing, so cutting them down or burning them both releases carbon they’ve been storing, as well as removes their ability to clean the air.

During a typical bikepacking trip, I have had the opportunity to bike through some of the most spectacular places on earth. Some places I have been able to bike because of the existing infrastructure, but most of the time I have had to scrounge for a place to stay, and even then, I am often not able to bike the whole way. Bikepacking is an opportunity to take an extended trip, usually a multi-week trip, with a small group of cyclists. At the end of the day, biking is what I do.

What is bikepacking?

bikepacking is the combination of cycling and backpacking. It requires a bike, camping (usually off-season), and a backpack. Most bikers have a tent or two as well.

What is bike touring?

bike touring is a long trip, usually a multi-week trip, in which you bike the whole way. The goal is to get as far as possible in a given timeframe. You usually stay in town-like accommodations.

Why would I do bikepacking?

bikepacking is dangerous. You don’t have the luxury of being able to stop and rest when you need to. You have to make each mile count.

New to bikepacking?

Here are a few things to consider:

bikepacking is for everyone! Everyone should try it.

bikepacking is not about racing. It is about enjoying the journey.

bikepacking is about community. You will ride with more people on a bikepacking trip than you would on a road trip.

bikepacking is about self-sufficiency. You will be on your bike for the majority of the trip.

bikepacking is about being in the moment. You will be in the mountains, among the pine trees, and take in the beauty around you.

bikepacking is about biking. You will be riding your bike, every day.

How do I go about bikepacking?

I have been bikepacking for over 15 years. I have been on over 300 bikepacking trips. These are the things I have learned along the way.

Get a bike. You need a bike to do bikepacking. You will be carrying your own gear and food
label: The bikepacking movement became popular in the 2010s. Compared to traditional bike touring, which has been popular for decades, bikepackers typically carry less and lighter equipment. The lighter load makes it easier to ride off-road. However, the equipment, such as frame bags, is often more expensive than traditional panniers. Furthermore, the limited storage space of bikepacking setups promotes an even more minimalistic lifestyle.

Q:

git - merge two branches without a common ancestor

I have a situation where I'm trying to merge two branches without a common ancestor.
So I have a master branch and a dev branch. I'm trying to merge dev to master without dev having a common ancestor with master.
I tried:
git merge dev

and 
git merge --no-ff dev master

but both of these approaches result in the dev branch having a common ancestor with master.
Any ideas on how I can achieve what I'm trying to do?

A:

You can't merge a master branch into itself. You can merge master into a merge-tracking branch (e.g. dev), but you can't merge dev into master.
You can merge dev into dev, but you can't merge dev into master.
You could create a new branch off the master branch (e.g. branch dev-master) and merge dev into that:
git checkout dev
git merge dev
git checkout master

How do I get the best backcountry skiing?

There is no set formula for backcountry skiing. It’s entirely down to the individual, as everyone has different needs and goals. There are some basic things to consider, though.

The right location for your trip depends on your skills, the area you’re looking to ski and the length of time you’ll be away.

If you’re new to backcountry skiing, you’ll need to build up your skills, as you won’t be comfortable in the wilderness if you haven’t skied for a while. If you’re an advanced skier, you’ll want to choose a trip that’s close to your level of skiing ability.

Your trip will also depend on the weather. If you’re planning a backcountry ski trip for the summer, you’ll want to choose a location that has decent snow and a reasonable chance of being snowed in.

If you’re heading to an alpine region, you’ll want to choose a place that has good snow and is close to a road for transport.

The cost to ski backcountry depends on the location, the length of your trip, the facilities and the number of people.

Square One

Square One (foaled 1 February 1992) is an Australian Thoroughbred racehorse and sire. In a racing career which lasted from 1995 to 1999 he ran eight times and won two races. In July 1995 he won a race over 2000 metres at Warwick Farm Racecourse and was then exported to Europe where he won the Prix Jean Prat in France. In the following year he was beaten in four of his nine races, including the Group One Matriarch Stakes but he did win the Group Two Glorious Stakes at Ascot Racecourse. He was then retired to stud where he had limited success as a breeding stallion.

Background
Square One was a bay horse with a white blaze bred in New Zealand by his owner Garry Allen. He was sired by the Australian horse Wildfire who won the Derby Stakes in 1982 and the Molecomb Stakes in 1983 before becoming a successful breeding stallion. Square One's dam, Hidden Secret won several races before becoming a successful broodmare. His first foals were born in 1993 and he was retired from racing to become a breeding stallion in Australia.

Racing career

1995: two-year-old season
Square One made his racecourse debut in a 1400 metre race over 1800 metres at Randwick Racecourse on 8 September and finished fifth of the eight runners behind City Nights. Wednesday, January 17, 2007

Alaska's Oil Production Cut in Half

Back in May, Alaska's oil production, at a record high of 1.7 million barrels per day, was cut in half. At the same time, the harsh winter that Alaska experienced, which included a huge drop in the amount of oil produced, just put Alaskan oil production at 1.2 million barrels per day.

The production cut was due to the fact that oil is hard to reach and refine during the winter months. Alaska's oil production is extremely dependent on the weather, as we have discussed before.

The fact that the cut was only temporary is interesting, and should be of great concern to everyone who is interested in energy prices. In the United States, we have a dependence on oil for heating, and the oil that we import from Alaska comes at a high price.

I'm sure that the media will be all over this story, and I'm sure that the Obama/Lieberman ticket will be making hay in the next couple of months.

The story is a good one for Obama, as it shows him as tough on energy and as a man of action. I'm sure that it will also be an excellent story for Lieberman and for the Democrats.

Of course, it may be a bit too early for such an issue to be a big issue in our elections, but I don't want to be too sure. The more attention this gets, the more likely it is that it will become a major issue in the campaign.

He has published nearly 70 papers related to tobacco. What are the three main states of matter and how does it transition between them?

3 main states of matter

States of matter

There are three main states of matter: solid, liquid and gas. It is the change in the state of matter that allows the matter to move from one state to another. There are different terms and names used to describe the states of matter. However, in this article, the terms used are solid, liquid and gas.

The three main states of matter

Solid

A solid is a form of matter that does not flow and does not change shape. When solid matter is pressed and put into a liquid it will float on top.

Solid state

A solid is a form of matter that does not flow and does not change shape. When solid matter is pressed and put into a liquid it will float on top.

Liquid

A liquid is a form of matter that moves easily and will flow.

Gas

A gas is a form of matter that does not move easily and will not fill up a container. Gas is made of particles which are very small.

Transition between states of matter

The changes between the states of matter are caused by the different energy levels. At the lowest energy level (absolute zero), all the particles are in the same energy level. This will make the particles of the same energy level repel one another.

This will cause the particles to stay in the solid state. However, as the temperature of the system increases, the particles will become more energetic. The particles will gain enough energy to break up the solid and move onto the liquid state.

The change from the solid state to the liquid state is called melting. This is because there is a change in the solid state to a liquid state.

However, at very high temperatures, the particles will gain enough energy to break up the solid and move onto the gas state.

The change from the liquid state to the gas state is called boiling. This is because there is a change in the liquid state to a gas state.

Liquid state to solid state

At very low temperatures, the particles will gain enough energy to break up the liquid and move onto the solid state.

Liquid state to gas state

At very high temperatures, the particles will gain enough energy to break up the liquid and move onto the gas state.

The invention provides a method for detecting and correcting faults in pipelines as well as the equipment suitable therefor, which can be realized as a system comprising at least two pipelines which are at least partially connected together.
The method according to the invention can be used in particular for detecting and correcting faults in pipelines of the type having a pipeline which is at least partially formed by iron tubes. The pipelines can in particular be pipelines for the transport of fluids, such as oil, gas, water, etc.
In the case of such pipelines, it is possible that, in and along the pipelines, there may be faults, such as coal-bed methane, especially methane containing inclusions, which can cause the pipeline to leak at corroded points.
In the case of pipelines of the type described above, the present invention is distinguished by the fact that the pipeline can be inspected in a non-destructive manner.
An inspection system according to the invention for inspecting pipelines as described above comprises a continuous optical fiber cable which comprises at least one optical fiber and is arranged such that, when the cable is advanced in the pipeline, the optical fiber is scanned with light pulses.
The scanning of the optical fiber is effected such that the light pulses are reflected by the moving cable and detected as a function of the distances between the light pulses and the scanning position. The result of such a scan is a signal which is used for the analysis of the quality of the pipe wall.
The optical fiber may be a single fiber or an array of fibers.
The light pulses may be generated by means of a light emitting diode which is arranged in the cable.

.io/k8s/

## Requirements
* Docker
* Kubernetes
* Helm

## How to get started
1. Install Docker
```
$ curl -sSL https://get.docker.com/ | sh
```

2. Install Kubernetes
```
$ sudo curl -SLO /tmp/bootstrap.sh https://get.k8s.io/v1.0.0/bootstrap.sh
```

3. Install Helm
```
$ curl -SL https://get.helm.sh/helm-v2.7.0-linux-amd64.tar.gz | tar -xz --strip-components=1
$ helm install k8s/k8s --version 2.7.0 --name k8s
```

4. Create a secret
```
$ kubectl create secret generic k8s-secrets --from-literal "foo=bar"
```

5. Create a pod
```
$ kubectl run nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2
```

## How to run tests
1. Install Kubernetes
```
$ docker run -it --rm -v "$(pwd):/test" -v "$(pwd)"/k8s:/root/.helm k8s/k8s
```

2. Install Helm and Kubernetes
```
$ helm install k8s/k8s --version 2.7.0 --name k8s
```

3. Run the test
```
$ kubectl run nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2
```

## How to run tests on Kubernetes
1. Create a secret
```
$ kubectl create secret generic k8s-secrets --from-literal "foo=bar"
```

2. Create a pod
```
$ kubectl run nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2
```

3. Run the test
```
$ kubectl run nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2
```

## Why not just use Docker?

1. K8s can run on a variety of different platforms, including Docker, AWS EC2, and a variety of other servers

The color white is created when all colors in the visible spectrum are combined in equal amounts. This can be seen in a prism or a rainbow, where sunlight is separated into its component colors. When all these colors are combined, the result is white light.

In terms of pigments, white can be created by using a substance that reflects all colors and absorbs none. A volume mount is a way to mount a volume into your container. You can think of it like a folder in Finder, except instead of writing to the file system, you are writing to a separate block storage layer. You can think of it as a piece of the host's file system that is only visible to the container.

You can use the volume mount to access the volume that was mounted, or you can use it to mount a directory inside the volume that contains files or data.

How do I mount a directory inside the volume that contains files or data?

When you mount a volume, Kubernetes creates a subdirectory inside the volume that contains the actual files that were stored on the volume. So, for example, if you have a volume named "myvolume" that was created with the path "/mnt/myvolume", then you can mount the directory "/mnt/myvolume/data" into your container by running:

$ kubectl run ndc --image=nginx --volume=myvolume --mount type=bind,source=data,target=/data,readOnly=true

You are going to get some great advice here.

I've been in the same spot as you. I had been using my iPhone for years, but
ended up with a Nexus 5. It's fantastic. I can't recommend it highly enough.

If you want to get back to the iPhone, I'd recommend that you do the normal
things people do when they switch devices:

1\. Set up a mail account on your new phone.

2\. Drop all of your other email accounts and social media accounts. You'll
find that you'll be using your new device primarily for checking your email,
so you can then use Google's excellent Inbox app to manage all of your
messages.

3\. Switch your main phone number to your new one.

4\. Set up Chrome/Firefox/Chromium on the new device.

5\. Use whatever online banking services you have on the old phone.

6\. Set up whatever online payments you use on the old device.

7\. Download all your apps for the new device.

8\. Set up your Gmail inboxes to sync the two devices.

9\. Set up all your calendar events on the new phone.

10\. Set up all your contacts on the new phone.

11\. Enable two-factor authentication on the new device.

12\. Set up every password you need on the new device.

13\. Set up your new phone to automatically backup to Google Drive.

14\. Enable an additional Google account on the new device, and sign into
that.

Once you have all that configured, I'd drop the old device and wait for the
new one to arrive. You will then have a nice clean slate to begin again.

A:

As @Migration2000 mentioned, the simple past is the most common way to write Norwegian.
The official translations of the Norwegian language into other languages is through a specific process called "Norwegianisation" (or "Norwegianisation" in English), and this process is unique for each language. The process is based on changing grammatical and syntactical rules from Norwegian to the language it is being translated into.
In case of Norwegian, this process is called "Norwegianisation", and it is done by the Norwegian Government.
You can read more about Norwegianisation of English, here.
In the case of German, this process is called Deutschsprachigen Übersetzung, and is done by the German Government. You can find more detailed information on the process of Germanisation, here.

A:

The official forms of Norwegian are the standardized written forms in the language, and the written forms are always in the third person plural (persons).
If your Norwegian is good enough, you may use the full plural form, but it is not common.

In genomics, a genome-wide association study (GWA study, or GWAS), is an observational study of a genome-wide set of genetic variants in different individuals to see if any variant is associated with a trait. GWA studies typically focus on associations between single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) and traits like major human diseases, but can equally be applied to any other genetic variants and any other organisms.

When applied to human data, GWA studies compare the DNA of participants having varying phenotypes for a particular trait or disease. These participants may be people with a disease (cases) and similar people without the disease (controls), or they may be people with different phenotypes for a particular trait, for example blood pressure. This approach is known as phenotype-first, in which the participants are classified first by their clinical manifestation(s), as opposed to genotype-first. Each person gives a sample of DNA, from which millions of genetic variants are read using SNP arrays. Duke University, a major research institution in Durham, North Carolina, has named its new school of public policy after former U.S. Representative Sanford Bishop (D-NC).

The school's name was announced June 11, 2013, in a ceremony at the Duke University Chapel.

Bishop, who served in the U.S. House of Representatives from 1953 to 1959, was a champion of civil rights and economic fairness for African-Americans.

He was also a member of the U.S. House Appropriations Committee, and was a member of the powerful House Ways and Means Committee. Bishop was also a leader of the civil rights movement in the 1950s and helped to organize the 1956 Nobel Peace Prize ceremony for Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. He was also a sponsor of legislation to extend voting rights to African-Americans.

Bishop resigned from Congress in 1959 to become general counsel of the NAACP Legal Defense Fund. He was appointed to the U.S. Court of Appeals in 1960 by President John F. Kennedy. In 1963, he became the first African-American to be elected to the North Carolina Court of Appeals.

Upon his election to the U.S. House in 1953, Bishop was the only African-American in the U.S. Congress. He was the first African-American to sit on the Judiciary Committee, and the first to serve on the House Committee on Appropriations.

Bishop said in a prepared statement that he was "deeply honored" to have his name associated with the school.

"Duke has long been a model of excellence in higher education, and I will be glad to have my name associated with this institution," he said. "I am deeply honored to be associated with this school. Public service has been a central part of my life since I was a young lawyer, and it will be a major part of my life in retirement."

The Sanford School at Duke is the first of its kind in the U.S. and the first public policy school in the United States to be named after an African-American public official.

"It is fitting that the school is named after Sanford, a Jew who rose to prominence in the civil rights movement and who championed civil and economic rights throughout his career. It is fitting, also, that the school is named after Sanford because he was a student at Duke and he

Immediate Payment Service (IMPS) is an instant payment inter-bank electronic funds transfer system in India. IMPS offers an inter-bank electronic fund transfer service through mobile phones. The service is available 24x7 throughout the year including bank holidays. NEFT was also made available 24x7 from December 2019. RTGS was also made available 24x7 from 14th December 2020.

It is managed by the National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI) and is built upon the existing National Financial Switch network. In 2010, the NPCI initially carried out a pilot for the mobile payment system with 4 member banks (State Bank of India, Bank of India, Union Bank of India and ICICI Bank), and expanded it to include Yes Bank, Axis Bank and HDFC Bank later that year. IMPS was publicly launched on 22 November 2010. Currently, there are 53 commercial banks, 101 Rural/District/Urban and cooperative banks, and 24 PPIi signed up for the IMPS service.

Need tips on river cruises?

River cruises are a popular way for travelers to experience the natural beauty and culture of European countries, and they're not hard to book. That said, there are a few things to keep in mind to help ensure you get the best cruise possible.

Most river cruises are priced per person, and while you can save money by booking your own cabin, there is no substitute for the experience of staying on a river cruise ship. You can occasionally find bargains if you're willing to pay a bit more. And if you absolutely must have the best cabin, there are several classes of ships, the best of which are luxury ships.

Not all river cruise ships are the same. While luxury ships are the most expensive, they provide the best cruise experience. Smaller ships, often called deluxe ships, are the least expensive, but they're also the least spacious. Some travelers prefer the coziness of the smaller ships, but the best river cruises are provided by the largest ships out there.

The best river cruises are the ones that include not only the cruise itself, but also shore excursions. While you can explore ports on your own, the best tours are provided by the cruise company.

River cruises are great for families and children, but there's no guarantee that your kids will be able to take part in all the activities. While some cruises include activities for all ages, most require that you book off-site activities.

Since river cruises are a shared experience, the best cruises are those that have a good balance between passengers and crew. While the cruise line may provide an upscale restaurant, the crew restaurant may be much more fun. And if you're a first-time cruiser, you're likely to get a taste of the culture more quickly by learning from the crew.

A brokerage account is a type of investment account that allows you to buy and sell stocks and other securities through a financial intermediary.

In order to purchase stocks and other securities, you must first open an investment account with an investment firm or broker.
A brokerage account is also called a securities account or a securities account.

There are three main types of brokerage accounts:
1. Regular brokerage account -- an investor can buy and sell securities without paying a commission to the broker.
2. Discount brokerage account -- an investor can buy and sell securities without paying a commission to the broker.
However, the investor pays a fee to the broker for each trade.

What is a Stock Broker?

What is a stock broker? A stock broker is a person or firm in the business of buying and selling stocks. They are the middlemen between the individual investor and the corporate issuer which issues stock.
The stock broker works with the corporate issuer to help the individual investor buy or sell shares of stock.
Who are stock brokers? Stock brokers can be individuals or they can be firms. Brokers can be full-service, or discount. Full-service brokers provide all the services a brokerage firm does, including research and advice. label:
The stock market helps companies raise money to fund operations by selling shares of stock, and it creates and sustains wealth for individual investors.

Companies raise money on the stock market by selling ownership stakes to investors. These equity stakes are known as shares of stock. By listing shares for sale on the stock exchanges that make up the stock market, companies get access to the capital they need to operate and expand their businesses without having to take on debt. In exchange for the privilege of selling stock to the public, companies are required to disclose information and give shareholders a say in how their businesses are run.

Investors benefit by exchanging their money for shares on the stock market. As companies put that money to work growing and expanding their businesses, investors reap the benefits as their shares of stock become more valuable over time, leading to capital gains. In addition, companies pay dividends to their shareholders as their profits grow.

The performances of individual stocks vary widely over time, but taken as a whole the stock market has historically rewarded investors with average annual returns of around 10%, making it one of the most reliable ways of growing your money.

In my experience, rabbits are not by nature very talkative. In fact, they are quite shy and reserved. They don’t like to be handled, and they are seldom willing to walk around with their head held high. They are also very sensitive to the presence of other animals (especially dogs), and it can be quite a challenge to get them to interact with other canines.

That said, if you are willing to be patient and keep your bunny motivated, she will surprise you with her advanced communication skills.

I have a friend who has a rabbit named Wes. When Wes was a baby, he was quite the talker. He would try to hop up on my lap and put his head in my hand, and he would try to talk to me.

The most common phrase I heard from him was “moo”! He would moo at anyone who came into his room, and he would moo at anyone who passed by. He would moo at the door if he didn’t like the way you were looking at him, and he would moo at the door if you didn’t answer his “hello”. I always thought that was pretty funny.

However, one thing that Wes didn’t like to do was to be petted. I tried everything to get him to do it, but it just wasn’t happening. One day, we decided to try a different tactic, and we went to the local pet store and bought a treat, a piece of carrot, and a bag of dry food. We also bought some treats for Wes to eat when he was in bed.

The Great Depression is a period of severe economic crisis in the United States that begins in late 1929 and lasts for about seven years. It was named the Great Depression because it was the worst economic depression in the history of the United States; the worst since the Panic of 1873.
It was a result of the stock market crash of 1929 that has been called the worst crash in the history of the United States.
The stock market crash was caused by the bank failures, which began in mid-October 1929.
It was also caused by the collapse of the U.S. economy, which was centered in the automobile industry.
The U.S. economy was already in a crisis in the early 1920s, and it continued to decline in the 1920s and 1929. The stock market crash was accompanied by a worldwide depression of business activity.

As you asked for a term, I would say that the Great Depression in its entirety lasted from 1929 to 1933.  It's also known as The Roaring Twenties (or "The Jazz Age") because of the prevalence of jazz musicians and other cultural advances in that decade.  The Great Depression is the most notable depression in U.S. history and is often credited with having been the catalyst for the start of the Second World War.

The book has a section called "Mudhayyalat al-‘Ibriyyah wa al-‘Ibriyyah" (The Rulers and Cities of Yemen).  The first part of the book is a list of the major rulers of Yemen, starting with the Hāshimid dynasty and going through the various dynasties. label: Oxidation reduction potential or ORP is measurement for water.  A millivolt meter can measure ORP and it is a measure of the potential of water to carry or hold antioxidants.  It is not a guarantee of antioxidants in water.  One form of antioxidants in water is free floating dissolved hydrogen.  A good analogy of antioxidants in water is the following: ORP is like a big swimming pool of potential but at the moment its currently empty and dissolved hydrogen is like ball of finite size.  The larger the ORP'swimming pool' the more dissolved hydrogen 'balls' can fit in that pool.  An ORP with a large negative value is huge swimming pool, and an OPR with a high positive value is no swimming pool.  ORP can also measure whether water is acidic or alkaline.  ORP that is negative tends more toward alkaline water, and ORP which is positive tends more towards neutral water and acidic water.

input: Where is Meherpur Sadar
label: Meherpur Sadar (Bengali: মেহেরপুর সদর) is an upazila of Meherpur District in the Division of Khulna, Bangladesh. Meherpur is the smallest district of Bangladesh in the South-western part within the Khulna Division. Before the partition in 1947, Meherpur was a part of the Nadia district of undivided India. Before 1984, it was a subdivision of Kushtia district. Meherpur consists of 1 municipality, 9 wards and 72 mahallas, 3 upazilas, 18 union parishads, 277 villages, 190 mouzas. The upazilas are Meherpur Sadar, Gangni and Mujibnagar.

label: The United States Bill of Rights comprises the first ten amendments to the United States Constitution. Proposed following the often bitter 1787–88 debate over the ratification of the Constitution and written to address the objections raised by Anti-Federalists, the Bill of Rights amendments add to the Constitution specific guarantees of personal freedoms and rights, clear limitations on the government's power in judicial and other proceedings, and explicit declarations that all powers not specifically granted to the federal government by the Constitution are reserved to the states or the people. The concepts codified in these amendments are built upon those in earlier documents, especially the Virginia Declaration of Rights (1776), as well as the Northwest Ordinance (1787), the English Bill of Rights (1689), and the Magna Carta (1215).

output:
'
---

Introduction
============

The discovery of planetary systems around other stars is one of the most exciting recent developments in astronomy. The fact that planets are so common around other stars gives us a unique chance to study and understand the formation and evolution of planetary systems, as well as the physical processes that lead to their formation.

Some of the most important questions in planet formation are whether planetary systems are common, and what characteristics do systems with planets have compared to those without.

Some of the most important questions in planet formation are whether planetary systems are common, and what characteristics do systems with planets have compared to those without.

The existence of multiple planets around the same star is now well established. The most recent results from the Kepler Mission [@borucki2013] show that at least one planet is detected in around 60 percent of all FGK-stars [@fressin2013].

The Kepler Mission
==================

The Kepler Mission [@borucki2013] is a space-based observatory with the mission goal of detecting Earth-like planets with periods between 20 and 80 days. The data collected by the spacecraft are searched for periodic signatures of periodic starspots, which would cause transit-like signatures in the light curves of the target stars.

The spacecraft continuously performs photometry of a set of 115 targets, which includes main-sequence and sub-giant stars, as well as red giants, white dwarfs, and eclipsing binaries.

The Kepler Mission consists of a spacecraft which orbits the Earth and continuously monitors a set of 115 targets. The spacecraft continuously performs photometry of a set of 115 targets, which includes main-sequence and sub-giant stars, as well as red giants, white dwarfs, and eclipsing binaries.

The Kepler spacecraft is based upon the bus design of the Explorer 1 spacecraft, and is built in the US by Ball Aerospace & Technologies Corporation. The spacecraft is launched on a Delta II rocket from Vandenberg Air Force Base, CA, USA, and is operated from the Ames Research Center in Moffett Field, CA, USA.

The Kepler mission has greatly improved our understanding of the formation of planetary systems. The measurements of the transit time-correlations in the Kepler data, as well as the analysis of the transit signals, have led to the detection of multiple planets in systems around some of the brightest stars in the Kepler data [@borucki2011; @batalha2013; @burke2015].
label: To be considered a planet the object must have an orbit around a sun, have enough mass to form a mostly round shape, and must be the dominant gravitational force in the area with no other similarly sized objects that are not orbiting the object in question.

s from The RunaroundTrying to give a shout out to the one and only albinos in the game. I went and got a picture of the albino direwolf, and since I know the whereabouts of the other one, I'll be uploading that tomorrow.

If you want to see more of these pics, head on over to my facebook page for a gallery of them.

I've tried to contact the maker of the TV show to get the name as well, but it seems that they don't have a name for them.

Monday, April 25, 2011

So, my friend, who I had previously mentioned that I would be getting a job at, called me up a few days ago to tell me that they are no longer hiring. The whole reason why I got the job is because they were looking for an artist and I was the best artist in the group, and they wanted me to be the artist. So, I was pretty upset, but I tried to keep my cool and act like it wasn't a big deal.

I was on the phone with them, and I told them that I would keep looking for things, but they told me that they were gonna have to let me go. I don't know why they would make me feel like I was going to be let go if they were still looking for artists, but I guess that's the way business works. They said that they told me that I was a good artist before, but they didn't find anything in their search to keep me.

Now, here's the thing. I hate to admit this, but I'm one of those people who hate it when people tell me that something wasn't good enough or they didn't like something I did. I mean, it's not like they are trying to be mean or anything, they could just be honest and tell me that they didn't like something I did. But instead, they just look at me like I'm crazy, and they say things like "You know, I like your work, but..."

That's why I'm going to try my hardest to keep looking for jobs, but I'm not getting my hopes up. I haven't gotten any calls from anyone yet, and I'm still looking through the paper in the next few days. I might get a job, I might not, but I'm not gonna get my hopes up anymore. I'm just gonna keep looking, and if I don't get a call from anyone
label: The direwolf, Ghost, is the albino pup and is adopted by Jon Snow

The present invention relates to a method of forming a semiconductor device, and more particularly to a method of forming a semiconductor device in which a gate pattern is formed in a self-aligned manner by using a hard mask.
A metal oxide semiconductor field effect transistor (MOSFET) is a type of field effect transistor (FET) which includes a gate pattern consisting of a pair of conductive electrodes formed on a semiconductor substrate and spaced apart from each other. One of the electrodes is the gate electrode, while the other electrode is the source or drain region. The gate pattern is insulated from the semiconductor substrate by an insulating layer. The gate pattern includes a gate insulation layer provided above the semiconductor substrate, and a gate electrode formed on the gate insulation layer.
The gate electrode is generally formed of polysilicon, which is typically formed by using a chemical vapor deposition (CVD) method. However, the polysilicon gate electrode is easily damaged by an etching process for forming the gate pattern. To solve the problem, a hard mask for protecting the gate electrode
label: Many edible plants grow well in Maryland without human intervention including chickweed, purslane, dandelion, and lamb's quarters. All of these plants may volunteer in a typical suburban yard or empty lot and will grow without being watered or tended to. They are all edible and nutritious.

output:
ie

Toyota, Honda, Nissan, Volkswagen, Mazda, Mitsubishi, Subaru, and Kia are all great choices and all have reasonably sized cars. You can get a pretty nice thing for $25,000. You can get a good used car for $15,000-$20,000.

For a new car, I'd start with a used Camry or Accord and get the max you can afford.

Jr. is 4 and is small for his age, so a car seat should be fine. My kids are much older and much bigger and I still use Honda minivans.

If you don't want a minivan, the Mazda5 is a great choice. It's a small compact and has all wheel drive.

I'm not a fan of minivans but if you want one, Mazda5 is a great choice. I've had many Honda Odysseys (4 kids) and Honda CR-V (2 kids). They are a great car. My minivan was a Honda Odyssey.

If you get a reliable used car, you won't have too many problems with it.

, I was diagnosed with stage 3 breast cancer in December of 2010. This blog is my account of what's happening on the journey to beat breast cancer.
