Friday, July 30, 2010

For those of you who have not seen the commercial on TV, it has been showing non-stop since July 1st.

I guess I'm late to the game, because I've watched it twice already.

I'm glad I am not on the pill, because I'm sure I would have gotten pregnant by now.

I thought about my dad and how I wish I had spent more time with him. Also, I thought about my mom ... and how she was my rock.

I am also thinking about the woman who made the commercial. She is probably in her 40s and has breast cancer.

She is strong, she is surviving, she has a good attitude and she is not scared. I wish more people could be like her.

I know she is not cured, but she is beating it with no chemo or radiation. She is doing the things she wants to do.

I hope she has a long and healthy life.

label: Atmospheric rivers are relatively long, narrow regions in the atmosphere – like rivers in the sky – that transport most of the water vapor outside of the tropics. We examined the relationship of infectiousness of macaques with simian immunodeficiency virus (SIV) infection to the risk of transmission. For this purpose, we compared the infectivity and the mean CD4+ cell depletion in SIV-infected macaques that became infected after a controlled inoculation with SIVmac251 with those that became infected after a spontaneous infection with the same virus. The infected macaques were divided into three groups according to their infectiousness and CD4+ cell depletion. The group with the greatest infectiousness and the greatest CD4+ cell depletion was the group that transmitted SIV to four of five uninfected macaques, and the group with the lowest infectiousness and the lowest CD4+ cell depletion was the group that did not transmit SIV to any of the uninfected macaques. These results indicate that the risk of SIV transmission increases with infectiousness and CD4+ cell depletion. ame.

First, there is no way for you to carry a first-prize trophy with you.  Trophies have to be kept in a museum or other public facility, where they are on display.  This is a legal requirement; if the trophy is in your possession, you are breaking the rules.

input: What is a water hammer?
output:
.org waterhammer.org Water hammer is a sudden increase in the volume of water in a closed system.

The sudden increase in water volume leads to increased pressure on the water supply pipes, which may result in pipe bursts. Water hammer can cause damage to pipes, plumbing fixtures and other materials by causing them to vibrate.

The sudden rise in water pressure can also cause water to start flowing backward through a faucet.

When you turn on a faucet, a small amount of water comes out, but the flow increases rapidly. That's because water pressure builds up in your water supply pipe, until it reaches a maximum pressure.

The force of this pressure is called water hammer. If the supply pipe is too long, or if the pipe has a lot of friction, the water pressure is higher than the maximum pressure. The result is that the pressure inside the pipe suddenly changes.

Water hammer can cause pipes to burst. If the pressure in your water supply pipe is too high, the water supply pipe can burst.

You can avoid a burst pipe by installing a pressure reducing valve.

The most common type of pressure reducing valve is an aerator.

Other types of pressure reducing valves include:

However, snap traps do not prevent cockroaches from crawling into pipes.

The most effective way to kill cockroaches is to eliminate their food source.

You can remove food from the home by sealing food containers.

Also, you can seal the food supply pipes and change the water supply to a system that does not have any food.

For example, it may be easy to close a water valve. Yet moments later it might explode from the sudden pressure of all the "upstream" water being forced to stop.

WEST CHESTER, Pa. – An East Price Hill woman was struck by a car while walking on the sidewalk.

Cheyenne White, who lives in the area, said she was crossing the street at the intersection of West Chester Pike and Jackson Pike, in the area of the Tower Shops, when she was hit.

White said she was walking across the street to catch a bus when she was hit.

“I fell to the ground and then I looked up and I saw a car coming at me and I asked ‘Did you see me?’ and the driver said ‘No, I didn’t see you,’” White said. “I just started screaming and the girl who was driving her car pulled over and she got out to check if I was okay.”

She said the driver then told her she had hit a pedestrian. The incident happened around 5 p.m.

Police said it appears White was crossing the street against a crosswalk, which is not safe.

“The traffic signal was not obeyed and the pedestrian was struck,” West Chester police said in a statement.

White was taken to The Children’s Hospital of Philadelphia. White’s injuries were not considered life threatening.

In the last few weeks, I’ve gotten a few questions about how to configure IntelliJ IDEA to use Maven, and how to make it work with a particular Maven repository. Hopefully, this blog post will help to answer those questions.

As with many other projects in the Java community, IntelliJ IDEA is written in Java and uses Maven as a build tool. IntelliJ IDEA also ships with a module that allows it to work with a particular Maven repository. In some cases, you may want to configure IntelliJ IDEA to use another Maven repository.

The following diagram explains the configuration of the IntelliJ IDEA module.

The IntelliJ IDEA module

In the IntelliJ IDEA module, there is a property called maven.settings.xml . This is the file where you can configure the module to use a particular Maven repository. The maven.settings.xml file contains the following lines:

<settings> <module> <id>idea</id> <activation> <property> <name>idea.settings</name> </property> </activation> <module> <id>idea-maven</id> <activation> <property> <name>idea.settings</name> </property> </activation> </module> <module> <id>idea-maven-data</id> <activation> <property> <name>idea.settings</name> </property> </activation> </module> </settings>

The ids of the two modules are defined as follows:

<module> <id>idea</id> <activation> <property> <name>idea.settings</name> </property> </activation> </module> <module> <id>idea-maven</id> <activation> <property> <name>idea.settings</name> </property> </activation> </module> <module> <id>idea-

In this study, we investigate the relationship between the histone variant H3.3 and DNA methylation during mammalian embryogenesis. H3.3 is a member of the histone H3 family that is deposited by the HIRA complex as the major variant in embryonic stem (ES) cells and is considered to be a marker of transcriptionally active chromatin. In contrast to other histone variants, H3.3 is not incorporated into chromatin, but its deposition is required for transcriptional activation by active enhancers. A recent study has shown that H3.3 is methylated at lysine 79 in ES cells, but not in differentiated cells. Since H3.3 is also methylated at lysine 4 and lysine 9 in differentiated cells, H3.3 methylation is suggested to mark a subset of genes that are silenced in differentiated cells.

To investigate whether H3.3 is involved in the maintenance of pluripotency in ES cells, we investigated whether H3.3 is methylated in ES cells. We found that H3.3 is methylated at lysines 4 and 9 in ES cells and that H3.3 methylation is maintained in ES cells in culture. However, demethylation of H3.3 seems to occur upon differentiation of ES cells, although epigenetic mechanisms are involved in the process. We also found that H3.3 methylation marks a subset of genes that are strongly expressed in ES cells, but are silenced in differentiated cells, and that genes whose expression is activated upon differentiation are not marked by H3.3 methylation.

To investigate the relationship between H3.3 methylation and the establishment of DNA methylation in ES cells, we analyzed the methylation status of H3K4 and H3K9 in ES cells and found that H3K4 methylation is detected in ES cells, whereas H3K9 methylation is not detected in ES cells. After differentiation, H3K4 methylation was lost and H3K9 methylation was newly detected in differentiated cells. These results indicate that H3K4 methylation is important for the establishment of DNA methylation during the differentiation of ES cells.

I've been eating pretty much nothing but meat and potatoes and with Thanksgiving coming up I need to add a little something to my diet. Ingredients

3/4 lb ground beef

1 can tomato sauce (I used Rotel)

1/2 head of cabbage, shredded

1/4 cup green onion, chopped

3 Tbsp sugar

3 Tbsp vinegar

1 Tbsp mustard

1 Tbsp salt

1/2 tsp garlic powder

1/4 tsp pepper

1/4 tsp celery seeds

3 Tbsp water

Directions

Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. You can either put it in a crock pot or use a big skillet to make it easier.

and

The artists that perform are typically up-and-coming artists who only play original music at the festival. Sets tend to be about an hour long, and they are hosted throughout the approximate 1-mile stretch of downtown Appleton on College Avenue at various coffee shops, bars, restaurants and parks.  A wide range of musical genres have been represented, including: rock, country, jazz, folk,  hip hop and circus punk.  Some performers come from the local area, such as Kyle Megna and The Monsoons.  Others are more regional performers, like Bascom Hill.  But many performers come from across the country, and have performed on multiple 'Miles', such as Chestnut Grove, The Quiet Hollers and Jamie Kent. Repeat bands often feel famous during the four days of the festival, leading Jamie Kent to write his song 'Famous (in Appleton)'. Once composted, what is the best time to put it in the garden? A good rule of thumb for vegetables is to put them in the garden when they are about 3-4 inches tall. This will give the roots a good start and the plant a chance to set a few roots down before the last frost.

How long does it take for a compost pile to break down? Some people will tell you that you should start composting as soon as you get it, but the truth is that it takes a bit longer to break down a pile of fresh food waste than it does one that has been sitting in a bin for a few months. To speed up the process, it’s a good idea to turn the pile every other day with a pitchfork, or with a shovel or garden fork. If you leave it alone for more than a few weeks, you should also add more kitchen scraps and other materials to the pile.

How can you tell if your compost pile is ready to use? At this point it’s a good idea to take a few handfuls of the compost and sit it on a piece of paper in a container. Let it sit for a day. If the material doesn’t crumble to pieces, it’s ready to use.

How can you keep your compost pile from stinking? It’s a good idea to have a little pile of sawdust with a little wood ash on hand, as well as a shovel or other digging tool. When you are digging holes for your compost pile, it’s a good idea to bring a couple of handfuls of sawdust into the hole to cover the waste so that it doesn’t attract flies.

How do you get rid of the smells in your compost pile? It’s a good idea to mix in some lime to the pile to help neutralize any unpleasant smells. You can also add blood meal and other organic matter to the compost pile to help absorb the smells.

Can you compost broken glass? Yes, you can compost it. Just be aware that if you put broken glass into your compost pile, it will eventually break down and release chemicals which are potentially toxic. So, you should avoid putting it in the compost pile.

input: What is Cuneiform?
output:
.org

Cuneiform, or cuneiform script, was a writing system used in the Middle East and Asia from approximately the 16th to the 12th centuries BC. It is the earliest known writing system to use wedge-shaped signs, and was the first to be devised with a systematic and consistent set of signs, although many variations on the system were used in different parts of the world.

Cuneiform writing is considered a precursor of the alphabet. It was devised in Mesopotamia, around the city of Uruk, on the banks of the Euphrates river, around the year 2800 BC. The system was developed over time by the Sumerians, Babylonians and Assyrians. In the later part of its existence, cuneiform became the main script for the Old Testament of the Bible.

Why was it used?

The Sumerians and Babylonians used cuneiform because they were in contact with one another. The Assyrians, however, used it as a way of reinforcing their power and control of the people of Mesopotamia.

Cuneiform was used as an artistic medium for all manner of things. But the principal use of cuneiform was in the form of seals. They were not only used to signify ownership, but also to seal contracts, and to seal letters.

The use of cuneiform in the script of the Bible

The Bible was written in Hebrew, Aramaic, Greek and other languages. Cuneiform was included in the Bible of the Old Testament. It is found in the Hebrew Old Testament, but often in difficult to translate English forms. The most common example of this is the word 'adam' which means 'man' in Hebrew. There are several translations into English for this word, but the one that is used most often is 'human', because it is used nearly 1,000 times in the Old Testament.

Cuneiform in the Old Testament

In the Old Testament, cuneiform script was used to write a number of things, such as:

The name of God, YHWH

The names of the twelve tribes of Israel, and their leaders

The names of the kings of Israel, Judah and the other tribes of Israel

The name of the city of Jerusalem

The names of the people of Israel

The names of the kings of Assyria, and the names of the kings of Egypt
label: Cuneiform is a logo-syllabic script that was used to write several languages of the Ancient Middle East. The script was in active use from the early Bronze Age until the beginning of the Common Era. It is named for the characteristic wedge-shaped impressions (Latin: cuneus) which form its signs. Cuneiform was originally developed to write the Sumerian language of southern Mesopotamia (modern Iraq). Cuneiform is the earliest known writing system.

In total, William Shakespeare wrote approximately 39 plays, each of which can be broadly categorized into three main groups: histories, comedies and tragedies. Henry V and Richard III are regarded amongst his finest histories, both featuring an English king as their eponymous character. The Tempest and A Midsummer Night's Dream are considered to be amongst his best comedies; whilst tragedies were arguably Shakespeare's greatest genre - Hamlet, Romeo and Juliet, Macbeth, Julius Caesar and King Lear are all amongst his finest contributions to this field. In the 1980s, the arcade was the hottest entertainment center in the world. Games were all the rage, and people paid to play them. The risk of getting caught playing a game at work seemed like it would be high, but I didn't think it would be that high. I had a part-time job at a local arcade, and one night, I got caught. I was working the register at the time, and I was cleaning up after a game when the owner came over and told me I was fired.

I was furious. I had always been proud that I had a job, and I didn't want to work at a place I didn't believe in anymore. I walked out of the arcade and immediately went to another part of town to see if there were any other jobs. I walked into a record shop, and the owner agreed to hire me on the spot. He knew I had just graduated from college and needed a job. He had me put together a portfolio of my work and came back the next day to give me a job. I worked there for a few years, and the owner would come in at nights to check on the place.

That's how I got my start in the video game industry. I was lucky. I had a job, and I was able to work at a place that was cool. I've worked in places where I wasn't lucky, and I've worked in places where there were good jobs, but no one cared about the games. I've worked in places where I was the only gamer, and I've worked in places where there were hundreds of gamers, but no one cared.

But the arcade was a special place. They were like a second home to me. I traveled to arcades in New York, New Jersey, and California to visit friends and play some games. It is defined as the projected area of the boundaries of the bounding box of the sample. The Isobaric Area in Volume (ISAV) is the surface area of the region defined by a fixed number of isobars in the same 3D X-Y-Z coordinate system. It is defined as the projected area of the contours of the isobars.

input: Where did Father's Day originate?
output:
a

I don't know the answer to this, but I do know what it isn't:

It isn't Mother's Day.

It isn't Father's Day.

It isn't even Boy's Day, which is more of a myth than a real holiday.

It is, in fact, April Fool's Day.

And like many other April Fool's Day traditions, it's not a day that is celebrated.

What is it?

Well, the origin of April Fool's Day may not be clear.

Some believe it all began in France.

There, on March 31, 1564, King Francis I decreed the celebration of April Fools' Day in his court.

As a prank, the French court would hide objects, like chairs and food, in the court's gardens, and then, when the king or his guests arrived, they would find the objects.

As a result, April Fools' Day was born in France, but not in the United States.

The concept of April Fools' Day might have started in the United States, though, when in 1683 the governor of the Massachusetts Bay Colony, Sir Edmund Andros, tried to convince the royal officials to stop celebrating what they called Mother's Day.

In the United States, Mother's Day was celebrated on the second Sunday in May in honor of the mother of Christ.

Andros suggested that they celebrate Father's Day instead, since it was also on a Sunday and he felt it should be observed just as Mother's Day had been.

Andros was sent to England to find Queen Anne, who agreed to make the change.

In England, the first Father's Day was celebrated in June.

But in the United States, the celebration didn't really catch on until the late 1800s, when the United States celebrated its Centennial.

The celebration of the United States Centennial in 1876 was called Father's Day.

And it was celebrated, at least in some cities, for the last time on June 21, 1876.

In the United States, Father's Day has been a day to honor fathers ever since.

Today, Father's Day is celebrated in many countries.

Here in the United States, we call it Father's Day, though it is also known as the Feast of the Fathers and the Feast of St. Joseph

Also remember that the longer the photo, the more the earth will turn, causing your starts to appear as trails in the photo - which may or may not be desired. For professional looking photos you'll need a telescope, and remember that no matter what you do, your photos won't look anything like those coming from Hubble and other large telescopes. Lastly, plan on spending plenty of time - the longer the exposure the better you can see the stars, and you might want to take several photos - try different parts of the sky

Airplane Incident is a 1956 British Empire thriller film, and the first in a long-running series of films produced by Hammer Films. It was Hammer's first colour film, and the first film to be filmed in Technicolor. The plot concerns the disappearance of a crew member on a commercial flight and the efforts of detectives to find him.

Plot

label: Many people say that being a grandparent is special.  They say it is special being a grandparent for a variety of reasons.  One very popular reason is they feel great pride in seeing their children grow into adulthood and take on the responsibility of having children. A second reason grandparents say their role is so special is they get to enjoy their grandchildren, and then return them to their parents who have the ongoing responsibility for raising the children. This creates a special bond between the grandparents and grandchildren that many grandparents describe as special.  A third reason many say it is special to be a grandparent is tied to an instinctive love they describe that they have for their grandchildren. You may hear them say, "I loved this grandchild from the minute I heard they were conceived, and the love has nothing to do with any merit, just love because they are my grandchild."  Having this love for another is a key factor in why it is special to be a grandparent.

The lateralization of brain function is the tendency for some neural functions or cognitive processes to be specialized to one side of the brain or the other. The median longitudinal fissure separates the human brain into two distinct cerebral hemispheres, connected by the corpus callosum. Although the macrostructure of the two hemispheres appears to be almost identical, different composition of neuronal networks allows for specialized function that is different in each hemisphere.

Lateralization of brain structures is based on general trends expressed in healthy patients; however, there are numerous counterexamples to each generalization. Each human's brain develops differently, leading to unique lateralization in individuals. This is different from specialization, as lateralization refers only to the function of one structure divided between two hemispheres. Specialization is much easier to observe as a trend, since it has a stronger anthropological history.

The best example of an established lateralization is that of Broca's and Wernicke's areas, where both are often found exclusively on the left hemisphere. Bonds provide the borrower with external funds to finance long-term investments or, in the case of government bonds, to finance current expenditure.

Finally sometimes babies just cry for no reason. Isn’t parenting fun?

label: I argue that differences in outcomes of credit scoring constitute both a data issue and an algorithmic bias. Let’s first examine the bias in the dataset. I think of the model itself as a black box that generates outputs to fulfill certain objectives – in the case of credit scoring, the objective is the accuracy, recall, and precision of default risk predictions. The model at its untrained version does not discriminate against foreign workers, women, or young people: in fact, it does not conceive of these (socially constructed) labels the way humans do. Yet, the dataset that the model is trained on is fraught with socially constructed biases. For example, social norms cast women as incapable, foreign workers as untrustworthy, and young people as inexperienced, leading to higher unemployment rate and worse living conditions for these groups. Their resulting higher historical default likelihood stems less likely from the demographics-related differences in capability than from the vicious cycles generated by social stereotypes. input: How can I help a homeless person?
output:
to another country and donate money to them?

A:

You can donate money to a charity that works with the homeless and similar situations.  You can also donate time doing things like helping clean up the streets (if you live in a busy city).
One of the easiest things to do, in my opinion, is to join a community organization that works with the homeless.  I live in a very large city, and we have a local organization called the Coalition for the Homeless.  They have a lot of programs that you can donate your time to, such as:

Going to soup kitchens for example
Helping transport people from shelter to shelter
Helping people with personal hygiene
Helping people with their pets (they have a pet library)
Helping people with their legal issues (if they have an immigration situation)
Helping people with their medical issues (if they have a medical problem)
Helping people with their financial issues (if they have a legal issue with their finances)

One thing I have done, is to help the homeless with their pets.  I help them get their animals healthy, and I help them with their medical and legal issues.  I feel like the homeless population is hurting, and I would like to help.
Another thing you could do is volunteer at a local shelter.  I volunteer at a local shelter, and I love it.  I help people get into the shelter, I help people get their pets into the shelter, I help people find clothes, I help people find food, I help people find jobs, I help people find housing, I help people find medical help, I help people find all sorts of things.  I get to meet new people, and I get to help people, and I feel like I have done something good.
You can also volunteer at a local soup kitchen.  I have done this, and I highly recommend it.  A soup kitchen is usually a place that has a lot of leftovers.  They feed it to people, and they help them by giving them things to do.  It's a lot of fun, and you meet a lot of people.  If you do volunteer at a soup kitchen, don't be afraid to ask people for whatever they can spare.  If they say no, then that's what you learn.  If they say yes, then you get to help.
One more thing you could do, is donate money to the Coalition for the Hom
label: There are lots of ways you can help a homeless person. Immediate help can be provided by giving them food and water and other essential items such as soap, shampoo, a toothbrush and toothpaste. Longer term solutions include giving money to a local food bank throughout the year.

input: What is Pullman National Historical Park?
label: Pullman National Historical Park is a historic district located in Chicago and was the first model, planned industrial community in the United States. It was built for George Pullman as a place to produce the famous Pullman sleeping cars.The park was made a national monument by president Barack Obama on February 19, 2015. The district had its origins in the manufacturing plans and organization of the Pullman Company and became one of the most well-known company towns in the United States, as well as the scene of the violent 1894 Pullman strike. During the strike the American Railway Union led by Eugene V. Debs boycotted the company following the panic of 1893 crippling railroad traffic in the United States. Thousands of U.S marshals and army troops were deployed to break up the strike. The strike ultimately changed the American labor landscape showing the power a union could have against an industry.

A:

In addition to the answers posted by @the_kludge and @Mankhool, I'll note that the use of dates to determine the year is quite common throughout history, and varies by region.
In Greece, the first is of course used, and it seems to have been a very important one.  The Roman calendar, which was the standard in the Western world for the first couple of millennia of the common era, was based on leap years.  But the Romans used what we might call "pure" years (each year is divisible by four, but not necessarily by 400).  So a year that was a multiple of 400 was a leap year, but a year that was a multiple of 400 that was not a multiple of 400 was not a leap year.  (Dates that were not divisible by 400 were sometimes rounded up or down, depending on whether they fell on the last or the first day of the year.  But if they did not fall on the first or the last day of the year, they were considered to be in the same year, just that one year in the history of the Roman empire was sometimes considered to have had two or more years.  For example, the year 476 is sometimes called "the year of the four emperors" because it had four emperors, but was sometimes called "the year of the two emperors" in order to avoid confusion.)
The year 587 was a leap year, as was the year 751.  The year 813 was not a leap year.  So 751 and 813 were both leap years, but the year 813 was not divisible by 400.  This is the case today in some years, but not all years.  In some years, the year 751 is a leap year, and in some years, it isn't.  In some years, the year 813 is a leap year, and in some years, it isn't, and so on.  So the number of leap years makes for a very good indication of when a year was a leap year.
The number of years divisible by 400, however, tells you nothing about whether or not a year was a leap year.  For example, the year 1700, which was a leap year, is also the year 2000, which was not a leap year.  The year ending in "00" is not a leap year.  So the number of years div

on the Internet and how that will help people to find information they need

each other, but we won't have that in the same way that we have that
information about celebrities, politicians, and sports stars. The average
person will be the celebrity of the Internet.

A: Well, people have always been interested in what other people are doing
and what they're interested in. Actually, the Internet is much more
intimate than television. The Internet is personal.

Q: How do you see the interaction between people on the Web as different
from the interaction on the Internet?

A: It's much more intimate. When I'm surfing the Web, I'm not looking for
information from a computer. I'm looking for information from other
people. That's why I'm here, and that's why I want to hang out with
people who are in the same boat.

It's a lot more intimate. They're not looking at you, they're looking at
something they really care about. It's not like television. It's a very
personal sort of interaction that people want to have.

Q: How is that different from e-mail?

you a message and you reply to that message. But I think there's more of a
sense of community in e-mail. It's like a real-life conversation. On

Zipporah is a Canaanite woman (see note at 2:1) from the tribe of Simeon (see Ge 49:3). She is the same woman who later in the story is referred to as "the wife of Reuel the Kenite" (Ge 30:24). Jethro is mentioned only here and in Exodus 18:1. He is the son of Horeb, the mountain where Moses and Aaron met after their exodus from Egypt. label: "March Madness" was originally coined after a high school basketball tournament in Illinois dating back to 1908. Henry V. Porter wrote an essay titled "March Madness" in the Illinois Interscholastic in 1939 to commemorate the tournament. Other media outlets embraced the term as the tournament continued to sell out and thrive for decades. Brent Musburger, a former sportswriter from Chicago, brought the term "March Madness" to the NCAA tournament when covering the event for CBS in 1982. The phrase became synonymous with the tournament ever since. In 2010, the NCAA made it official and paid IHSA (The Illinois High School Association) $17.2M for the rights to the phrase, and began using the trademark in marketing materials, logos and other branding material. While only used for the men's tournament for decades, the NCAA only began using the phrase "March Madness" for the women's tournament in 2022.

I’d never heard of either of them, and when I first saw their names in the credits, I thought they were a new addition to the movie.

The company they worked with was mostly made up of veterans of the U.S. military. Pitt and Scott were on set from early on, to help guide the production, and were the ones who decided which scenes would be included in the film. But it wasn’t just a story of Pitt learning to make a movie. It was a story of Pitt and Scott learning to work together.

The scene is a little awkward, because Pitt and Scott are strangers, and the shop owner is an unlikable jerk. Rare-earth materials are minerals that contain a small number of atoms of the element erbium. The rare-earth elements include ytterbium, neodymium, and praseodymium.

Aren't all rare-earth materials precious?

No. The rare-earth metals are not as rare as many people think. The four heavy rare-earth metals—the lanthanides—are found in small quantities in natural minerals. They are not typically found in ores or in large quantities in the earth's crust. Rare-earth metals are most plentiful in low-temperature metamorphic rocks.

What is the difference between light and heavy rare-earth metal ores?

The lighter rare-earth metals are less stable in their ores than the heavy rare-earth metals. The lighter rare-earth elements can be melted and fused in the furnace at temperatures of about 1,500°C (2,700°F). The heavier rare-earth metals can be melted at lower temperatures.

What is a lanthanide?

The lanthanide series of the elements includes the first four elements of the periodic table: lanthanum, cerium, praseodymium, and neodymium. The lanthanide elements are named for the region of France where they were first discovered. The first lanthanide element, lanthanum, was discovered in 1857. The other three elements in the series were found by scientists at the Royal Institution of Great Britain in the late 1800s.

What is a lutetium?

The lutetium series of the elements includes the first four elements of the periodic table: lutetium, hafnium, lawrencium, and curium. The lutetium elements were discovered in the 1940s. The other three elements of the series were discovered by scientists at the Metallurgical Laboratory at the University of Chicago in the late 1900s.

What are the typical applications of rare-earth materials?

Rare-earth materials can be used in electricity transformers, magnets, light bulbs, and other electrical components. input: What are some examples of tasks performed by AI?
output:
it: What are some examples of tasks performed by AI?

A:

The simplest example is that of an agent that is in charge of a single task.
For example, a robot that is sent to the store to buy an item.

A:

Some examples I've come across:

Facial recognition - When I enter a room, I can just tell by facial recognition if there are any humans in it.
Predicting the weather - I'm in a room so I can tell you what the weather is like outside the window.
Handwriting recognition - I'm writing an email to you, I can just tell if it's from you.

A:

The basic problem of having a robot in the house is the following:

The robot is not doing anything useful.
The robot is doing something, but it is not what you want it to do.

For example a robot that just cleans the floor. How can you tell if it is cleaning correctly? If it's cleaning the right things (like the corners of the table) it is probably doing a good job. But if it is just cleaning any spot on the floor the robot is in fact doing nothing useful. The same could be done with the robot vacuum cleaner.

A:

As pointed out by others, the most basic is a robot that does housework - that is, cleaning and maintaining things.
But beyond that, you could have a robot that just picks up things and puts them into a location you want it in.  Perhaps you have a set of boxes and you want the robot to put them in the right place.  Or perhaps you want the robot to put them in the right place and the boxes are laying where you want them.
Or perhaps the robot knows where it is and where it is supposed to be putting things.
Or perhaps you want the robot to do the same kind of thing that a human does, but in a different setting.
In any of those cases, the robot is doing something, but it is not doing something you want it to do.
The most common problem with these kinds of robots is that they just do things they are told to do.  They do not know how to decide what is the best way to do that - what is the best way to get the boxes into the right place?  What is the best way to clean the floor?  What is the best spot to put the boxes?
label: Examples of tasks performed by AI include speech recognition, computer vision, translation between (natural) languages, and other mappings of inputs.

Technically speaking, very little music theory knowledge is “required” to compose music. Music theory is, essentially, what musicians have learned over the course of several hundred years about how to write music that is interesting and sounds good. In other words, music theory is there to help you, not hold you back. 

When you learn music theory, what often happens is that you expand your broader understanding of music, which can be a very helpful safety net. The more music theory you know, the easier you’ll be able to distinguish between the good ideas and the not-so-good. You need to know the rules before you can break them. You need to be able to write by the book before you throw the book away. If not, you run the risk of writing music that’s not nearly as clever as you think it is, that tries to be daring and experimental but ends up just being dull and vanilla. And frankly, I just don’t see the value in ignoring all the work that centuries worth of musicians have done into knowing how music works. Putting the time into learning and really understanding it can only make you a better musician and a better composer.

Significance of the Gay-Lussac scale

The Gay-Lussac scale is a useful tool in determining the melting point of a metal, and thus it is useful when molten metal is poured from a vessel.

A simple example is to take a metal, say tin, and immerse it in liquid mercury. The surface of the metal will begin to melt when the temperature of the mercury is approximately 910° Celsius. The original shape of the metal is recovered at 700° Celsius. This “melting point” is called the fluid-solid phase transition.

The Gay-Lussac scale is also useful at measuring the temperature of a nuclear fusion reactor. The temperature inside a fusion reactor is determined by how much energy the fuel contains. The temperature at which the fuel begins to melt is called the critical temperature. The Gay-Lussac scale can be used to determine the critical temperature.

The Gay-Lussac scale was invented by Jean-Victor Gay-Lussac (1778-1850). The scale was first published by Gay-Lussac in 1825 and soon after improved by Richard R. Straubel (1825-1898). This scale is named after him.

The Gay-Lussac scale is a logarithmic scale, where the value of K is governed by the Lambert-Beer law:

k = K0 ln(T/T0)

where k is the coefficient of thermal expansion, K0 is the coefficient of thermal expansion at reference temperature, T0, and T is the temperature of the material.

The coefficient of thermal expansion is a measure of the amount of change of length for a certain amount of change of temperature. For example, a metal that expands by a certain amount for every degree increase has the same value of the coefficient of thermal expansion as a metal that expands by a certain amount for every degree increase.

lista_palavras = ['palavra1', 'palavra2']

Diferença entre list comprehension e for comprehension

Como o @user2357112 disse, existe uma diferença entre um comando de compilação e outro comando de execução - o comando de compilação só executa uma vez e não precisa retornar nada; o comando de execução deve retornar algo, o que pode ser um objecto, um dicionário, seja qual for a sua estrutura.
O comando de compilação pode ser usado para iterar sobre a lista de forma iterativa, o que é muito útil para listas grandes - a lista pode ser gerada dinamicamente e de forma iterativa, o que nem sempre é fácil para as listas

Is it possible to show the date formatter in the success message when using Devise?

I want to show the date formatter in the success message.

A:

Looks like Devise uses the standard Rails Date formater to format the date.
You can override this behaviour by defining a custom date formatter:
config/initializers/devise.rb
Devise.setup do |config|
  config.date_formats = [:month_name, :day_name, :year_name]

  config.mailer_sender = 'devise@example.com'
  config.mailer_default_options = {
    config.date_formats = [:month_name, :day_name, :year_name]
  }
end

You can then use a custom formatter:
<%= f.date_field :date, :value => Date.today, :label => "Date", :input_html => { :class => 'date_field_with_js form-control' } %>

More information: http://apidock.com/rails

The measurement problem is a difficult problem, but the answers are worth understanding, if they are possible. Those answers are as follows:

1. Quantum theory is incomplete, as it has to be completed with various hidden variables.

2. Quantum theory is not a complete theory of reality.

3. Quantum theory is not a complete theory of information.

4. Quantum theory is not a complete theory of measurement.

The first reason is due to the fact that quantum theory does not describe the behavior of subatomic particles, but only of the probabilities of these particles to have certain definite positions and orientations in space. It is necessary to have a theory of the behavior of subatomic particles to obtain the answers to these questions.

The second reason is due to the fact that the theory of quantum physics is not a complete theory of reality. The most famous example is the EPR paradox. This paradox states that if we have a quantum mechanism that allows us to transmit a message instantaneously, then it is possible to send a message that is behind the other, since the message is sent instantaneously. This is impossible in classical physics, because there is no way of sending messages that are behind the other, unless you use a light beam (which is possible in classical physics, but not in quantum physics).

The third reason is due to the fact that quantum theory is not a complete theory of information. For example, in the famous experiment of Einstein, Podolsky, and Rosen (EPR), it is described that if a particle is entangled with a particle, then if you measure one of the entangled particles, it is possible that the other particle will be also measured. This phenomenon is called "nonlocality." In classical physics, entanglement does not occur, since it requires the simultaneous existence of two particles in the same space-time system.

The fourth reason is due to the fact that quantum theory does not describe the behavior of quantum measurement. We can deduce from the theory of quantum physics that any measurement must have an effect in the system, but we also know that quantum measurement also gives us the probability that the system will be in a certain state. It is not possible to say that the system will be in a particular state or not when we measure it. For example, the state of a protein molecule can be measured as "inactive" or "active," but it is not possible to say that it will be in an "active" or "inactive" state

3. The mathematical theories are all at an advanced level and few examples of how to actually apply them appear in text books.

5. The theory is based on either infinitely parallel actions occurring deterministically or statistical interpretation of a range of outcomes
6. All of these interactions occur without direct reference to space/time and so are in abstract spaces that need to be decided for the calculation and physically interpreted

input: What are some signs and symptoms of Type 2 Diabetes?
output:
Type 2 Diabetes Symptoms are listed below.

Signs and symptoms of Type 2 Diabetes

Overweight

Abdominal bloating

Decreased physical activity

Decreased or no energy

Fatigue

Frequent urination

Gastrointestinal (GI) problems

Increased hunger

Increased thirst

Increased urination

Increased vaginal discharge

Nausea

Polyuria (frequent urination)

Sleep disturbances

Sugar in the urine

Thin person

These are some of the most common signs and symptoms of Type 2 Diabetes.

How is Type 2 Diabetes diagnosed?

If you have any of the signs and symptoms listed above, you may have Type 2 Diabetes. The diagnosis of Type 2 Diabetes is made by a doctor. Blood sugar levels are measured in the blood. If they are higher than normal, it is considered Type 2 Diabetes.

How is Type 2 Diabetes treated?

There are many different types of treatment for Type 2 Diabetes.

Lifestyle changes: The goals of these changes are to lose weight, make healthier food choices, and increase physical activity.

Medication: Medications are often used to treat Type 2 Diabetes. Your doctor will choose the right medications for you based on your personal needs and your lifestyle.

Surgery: Sometimes, medication and lifestyle changes do not work well enough and you may need surgery.

What is the outlook for Type 2 Diabetes?

The outlook for Type 2 Diabetes depends on the person. Type 2 Diabetes can be controlled with lifestyle changes, medication, and surgery. If you have Type 2 Diabetes, it is important to manage the disease and take your medications as directed. If you don’t, you may risk developing serious complications.

What is the cure for Type 2 Diabetes?

The cure for Type 2 Diabetes is to manage the disease and take medications as directed. If you continue to take the proper medications and follow a healthy lifestyle, you should be able to prevent diabetes complications.Q:

Other symptoms that are commonly present at diagnosis include a history of blurred vision, itchiness, peripheral neuropathy, recurrent vaginal infections, and fatigue. Other symptoms may include loss of taste. Many people, however, have no symptoms during the first few years and are diagnosed on routine testing. A small number of people with type 2 diabetes can develop a hyperosmolar hyperglycemic state (a condition of very high blood sugar associated with a decreased level of consciousness and low blood pressure).

Hi Nick, I’ve just read your piece in today’s Guardian, and I couldn’t agree more with your comment about the 20th anniversary of the fight to free Kuwait. What struck a chord with me was the fact that it was the 21st of April, and I was born on the 22nd – thus I am a ‘shabbas goy’! I went to school with a lot of Israeli kids and was often mistaken for one, as they all looked very similar. I can’t say I’m very fond of them, but the fact that I have a Jewish background and a connection to Israel makes me very proud. Many of them are very gloomy people – not only about Israel, but also the world in general. I try to explain to them that a lot of people are suffering right now in the world and it’s not a very nice place, but from time to time I realise that they don’t care, and they’re happy to be in Israel and have their normal life.

I don’t know if you know the story of Uri Avnery, the Israeli writer, politician and peace activist. He was a soldier in the Israeli army for many years – apparently he saw a young Palestinian boy being beaten by an Israeli soldier, but didn’t do anything to stop it. I think this experience made him very angry, so he began to take part in demonstrations against the occupation. I was very moved by his speech at the commemoration of the liberation of Kuwait, and I think he has a point. He said that the West banks didn’t care until a few days ago what was happening in the world. I think we should all think about this – the West Bank and Gaza are very important to the rest of the world, but what is happening to the rest of the world is far more important to us.

Yours in peace,

Marilyn

How to get rid of the following warning in MySQL stored procedure:

I am getting a warning in my MySQL stored procedure. I am using MySQL 5.7.17.
I am using MySQL Workbench to write the stored procedure.
I am executing the stored procedure using the following query:
call Add_Item (32, 'a');

The stored procedure is as follows:
DELIMITER $$

CREATE PROCEDURE `Add_Item`(IN int_item_id INT, IN int_user_id INT)
BEGIN
INSERT INTO (`ordering_items` (`item_id`, `user_id`) VALUES (int_item_id, int_user_id);
END$$

DELIMITER ;

The warning is:

SQL command prepared without parameters

A:

You have to use prepared statements in MySQL.
Prepared statements in MySQL
You have to change your code to:
DELIMITER $$

CREATE PROCEDURE `Add_Item`(IN item_id INT, IN user_id INT)
BEGIN
    SET @sql = CONCAT('INSERT INTO `ordering_items`(`item_id`, `user_id`) VALUES (', int_item_id, ',', int_user_id, ');');
    PREP

The screenshot tool is not just limited to taking screenshots of the phone’s screen. It is also used to take screenshots of the keyboard, the lock screen, and the notification panel.

abstract: 'We are interested in the generalised Poisson algebra $C^\infty(M)[[\lambda]]$, where $M$ is a smooth manifold, and $C^\infty(M)$ is the algebra of smooth functions on $M$. As a vector space $C^\infty(M)[[\lambda]]$ is a direct sum of the Poisson algebra $C^\infty(M)$ and an infinite series of non-commutative power series. In this paper we study the behaviour of the Poisson algebra $C^\infty(M)[[\lambda]]$ under the action of the Lie algebra $\mathfrak{g}$ of vector fields on $M$ and the derivation $\delta$ of the algebra $C^\infty(M)$. We obtain necessary and sufficient conditions for the Lie subalgebra $\mathfrak{h}\subset\mathfrak{g}$ to be invariant. We also discuss a method of computing the invariant subalgebra $\mathfrak{h}$ using a representation of the algebra $C^\infty(M)[[\lambda]]$ as a power series in $\lambda$ and the derivation $\delta$.'

What is a meme, and why is it the new gene?

If you don’t know what a meme is, it’s because you’re not old enough to have seen it before!

A meme was first used by Richard Dawkins in his 1976 book The Selfish Gene to describe a unit of cultural or biological information passed down from one individual to another. It is a unit of cultural information that gets passed down from one person to another by imitation, and is a unit of biological information passed down from one organism to another through genes.

If you think of a gene as a ‘blueprint’, then a meme is the ‘soul’ of a culture – a blueprint for culture. Genes are also the ‘blueprint’ for an individual, but a meme is the ‘soul’ of a species. (Memes are also often called ‘cultural viruses’ – a term coined by Richard Dawkins – so it’s important to remember that a gene is a ‘cultural virus’ too!)

Here’s a really simple example of a meme…

Meme is a unit of cultural information that gets passed down from one person to another by imitation, and is a unit of biological information passed down from one organism to another through genes.

One well-known gene that influences Alzheimer’s risk is the apolipoprotein E (APOE) gene, which has been identified via Genome Wide Association Studies (GWAS). The APOE gene is involved in making a protein that helps carry cholesterol and other types of fat in the bloodstream.

Q:

Displaying Data from two tables and linking them with each other

I have two tables, one with user ID's and other with the status of the user. For example:
User ID   Status
1         1
1         2
1         3
2         1
3         2
2         3

I want to make a query that displays the status number of the user, but also displays the user ID who has the status. For example:
Status Number     User ID
   1                 1
   1                 2
   1                 3
   2                 2
   2                 3
   3                 1

I don't even know where to begin with this one.

A:

You should use a JOIN in your statement:
SELECT t1.status, t2.user_id
  FROM users AS t1
  JOIN users AS t2
    ON t2.user_id = t1.user_id
   AND t2.status = t1.status
 WHERE t1.user_id = 1

John Dassow, Jr. (August 10, 1845 – October 8, 1917) was an American farmer, manufacturer, and politician.

Born in what is now Mecklenburg, Germany, Dassow emigrated with his parents, in 1861 to the United States and settled on a farm in the town of Sheboygan Falls, Sheboygan County, Wisconsin. In 1864 and 1865, Dassow served in the 30th Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment during the American Civil War. Dassow was a farmer and owned the Sheboygan County Mills. He was also involved with cheese factories and the real estate business. Dassow served on the Sheboygan County Board of Supervisors and was chairman of the county board. He was also treasurer of the local school board. In 1893, Dassow served in the Wisconsin State Assembly and was a Democrat. In 1917, Dassow died at his house in the town of Sheboygan Falls from ill health.

input: Write a poem about a raven
label:
Once upon a midnight dreary, while I pondered, weak and weary,
Over many a quaint and curious volume of forgotten lore—
While I nodded, nearly napping, suddenly there came a tapping,
As of some one gently rapping, rapping at my chamber door.
“’Tis some visitor,” I muttered, “tapping at my chamber door—
Only this and nothing more.”

Ah, distinctly I remember it was in the bleak December;
And each separate dying ember wrought its ghost upon the floor.
Eagerly I wished the morrow;—vainly I had sought to borrow
From my books surcease of sorrow—sorrow for the lost Lenore—
For the rare and radiant maiden whom the angels name Lenore—
Nameless here for evermore.

Sound of the Sea, a collection of songs for piano written by Oleg Sentsov, is a rare and wonderful treasure. This recording was made while Sentsov was a prisoner in a Russian gulag.

"After a long and tiring flight, I had enough time to listen to the track a few times, and then I noticed the instrument was playing on its own. I was not in the mood to touch the piano; so I just sat down and listened to the track. I was mesmerized. After many years, I have no words to describe my feelings and emotions.

The title of the track is the sound of the sea, the sand, the wind, the waves. It feels like being on the seashore, listening to the sound of the sea.

The track is a symbol of hope, a symbol of freedom, a symbol of humanity.

The piano plays a fast and slow version of the track. It starts with slow and beautiful to the end and then starts to play a fast version of the track.

I believe that the recording of the track is a prayer, a message, a hope, and a wish from the heart of one of the prisoners that I met in the Gulag.

I would really love to thank you for giving this recording to the world.

Thank you" - Oleg Sentsov

This is a special release of Russian pianist Oleg Sentsov and the Sound of the Sea. This is a collective effort to help Oleg. The track is a compilation of songs written by Oleg Sentsov and performed by his friends and other musicians from around the world. The compilation includes tracks that were made with Oleg in the Gulag, in exile, in the West and in the Soviet Union.

PS: I am not affiliated with Oleg Sentsov, I am not a fan, I am just a fan of the music.

Background {#Sec1}
==========

Despite the fact that the number of malaria cases in Brazil has been falling since 2012, the disease continues to be a major public health problem in the country. Since the beginning of the 21st century, malaria has gradually become a chronic disease in the Amazon region, with the average annual number of cases ranging from 300,000 to 500,000 episodes \[[@CR1]\].

The Amazon region is the Brazilian territory with the highest incidence of malaria, where an estimated 60,000 cases of malaria occur annually \[[@CR1], [@CR2]\]. The Amazonian region, inclusive of the states of Acre, Amapá, Amazonas and Rondônia, is the largest Brazilian territory with the highest number of malarial cases in the country.

The Amazonian region includes some of the most heavily populated areas in the country, with about 8 million people living in approximately three million km^2^ \[[@CR3]\]. In this scenario, human activities are concentrated in cities and towns, where there is a large movement of people. This leads to human contact with mosquitos and a greater risk of transmission and consequently, a higher incidence of malaria \[[@CR4]\]. The population of the Amazon region is more heterogeneous than the population of other regions in Brazil, with a higher proportion of people of indigenous origin \[[@CR3]\].

In the Amazonian region, the main malaria vector is *Anopheles darlingi*, which is found in the peridomestic environment, where it is a well-adapted parasite to survive and develop in human blood \[[@CR5], [@CR6]\]. The epidemiological characterization of malaria in the Amazon region is of particular interest because it is one of the regions where malaria transmission is expected to be lower than in other regions of the country, especially in the southeast, where the transmission is considered to be under control \[[@CR7]\].

Therefore, it is important to understand the actual epidemiological situation of malaria disease in the Amazon region, what factors are associated with the disease and how the disease is distributed in the region. In this context, the
label: sbt is an open-source build tool for Scala and Java projects, similar to Apache's Maven and Gradle.

Part of my work as a cognitive behavioral therapist involves the use of cognitive-behavioral approaches to health care. Cognitive-behavioral approaches to health care are based on the idea that it is possible to learn new ways of thinking and behaving in order to help people change their feelings and behaviors that can negatively impact their health. In fact, cognitive-behavioral approaches to health care are based on the idea that the brain is malleable and that people can learn new ways of thinking and behaving that will help them improve their health.

How to find the 3rd and 4th largest elements in a list with O(n) time?

Given a list of numbers, I need to find the 3rd and fourth largest elements in O(n) time.
Example:
[1,2,3,4,5,6,7]
(in this list, 1,2,3,4,5,6,7 is the list)
Output:
4,5,6
3,5,6
4,5,6
5,6,7

Code:
static void Main(string[] args)
{
    List<int> numbers = new List<int>() { 1,2,3,4,5,6,7 };
    int max = numbers.Max();
    int 3rdMax = numbers.Select((x, index) => new { index })
                .OrderByDescending(n => n.index)
                .Where(n => n.index == max)
                .Select(n => n.x).First();
    int 4thMax = numbers.Select((x, index) => new { index })
                .OrderByDescending(n => n.index)
                .Where(n => n.index == max)
                .Select(n => n.x).Skip(1).First();
}

I am using .Select(n => n.x).First(); to get the 3rd largest number, but the it's taking O(n^2) time.

A:

You can use the following LINQ query:
var result = numbers.GroupBy(n => n)
    .Select(g => g.OrderByDescending(n => n.Key).First())
    .Skip(1)
    .Take(3);

The query groups the numbers by the key of the group, then orders them by descending key and takes the first three elements.
The query first takes the numbers 1, 2, 3, ... , N-1, the N-1 most sorted element, and then takes the first element from the remaining numbers.

input: What is Ayurveda?
output:
. Ayurveda is a Sanskrit word meaning ‘the science of life.’ According to Ayurveda, every human being is made up of three fundamental elements called ‘dhatu’—earth, water, and fire. These elements are held together by five elements called ‘tanmatra’—space, time, air, water, and ether. Ayurvedic philosophy perceives the human body as a microcosm of the universe. Ayurveda’s principles of balance and harmony apply to all aspects of daily life, including diet and exercise.Ayurveda has been around for centuries, and its principles are as sound today as they were centuries ago. Ayurvedic principles of nutrition, lifestyle, and healing are widely practiced in India and other parts of Asia, and Ayurvedic physicians are active in the United States.

Ayurvedic physicians understand that a person’s body is made up of a unique combination of dhatu and tanmatra. Each person’s dhatu is expressed differently. The elements in the person’s body are each assigned a specific role to play in the maintenance of health and well-being. When Ayurvedic physicians see a client, they take into account the dhatu, tanmatra, and asanas (postures) of his or her body. (For more information on Ayurvedic medicine, see the booklet The Basics of Ayurveda: A Practical Guide to Healing the Body.)

Ayurveda is based on the belief that the body is an expression of the mind and spirit. Certain foods are considered to be good for certain dhatus and tanmatras. According to Ayurvedic philosophy, a person’s happiness and health are linked to his or her lifestyle. For this reason, Ayurvedic physicians recommend a diet that balances all the dhatus, tanmatras, and asanas.

Sattvic foods are considered to be nutritious and are good for the mind and body. They are considered to be “cooler” than rajasic and tamasic foods. Sattvic foods are considered to be more conducive to a balanced mind and body. They include salads, vegetables, fruits, nuts, whole grains, and seeds (including sesame, chia, flax, and hemp). Sattvic foods are believed to be beneficial to both the body and the mind.

label: Ayurveda is a natural system of medicine that originated in India more than 3,000 years ago. The term Ayurveda is derived from the Sanskrit words ayur (life) and veda (science or knowledge). Thus, Ayurveda translates to knowledge of life. Based on the idea that disease is due to an imbalance or stress in a person's consciousness, Ayurveda encourages certain lifestyle interventions and natural therapies to regain a balance between the body, mind, spirit, and the environment.

There are non-deterministic Turing machines which recognize every possible input.
Let $\Sigma$ be the Turing machine alphabet, and $\Sigma^*$ the Turing machine alphabet with the empty string as an additional symbol.
A non-deterministic Turing machine $M$ is one which has an input $\sigma$ of the form $\sigma = \sigma_1 \cdots \sigma_n$ and an output $Y \in \Sigma^*$ and accepts if there exists $i \in \{1, \ldots, n\}$ such that $\sigma_i = \varepsilon$ and $Y = \sigma_1 \cdots \sigma_i$.
If $\Sigma$ is finite, and $X \in \Sigma^*$ is a string over $\Sigma$ of length $n$, then there is a non-deterministic Turing machine which recognizes $X$ and accepts if and only if $X = 0^n1$.

input: How do you play the game of LoL?
output:
How do you play the game of LoL?

What is LoL?

LoL (short for “League of Legends”) is a free-to-play, online multiplayer game developed by Riot Games for Windows (PC), Windows Phone, and Macintosh (Mac). LoL is a game of heroes, skills, and spells, where players select one of several champions (players) to control and lead their characters into battle. Each time players win a game, they are awarded with experience points (XP) that can be used to upgrade their champions’ skills. LoL can be played individually or with others in a variety of different “lanes” (servers).

The game is divided into two modes: “ranked” and “unranked”. Ranked games allow players to participate in ranked matches, which are generally more competitive and have better rewards for winning. Unranked games are for players who just want to have fun competing against their friends and other players.

What are the rules of LoL?

The rules of LoL are simple—a player controls a hero or a team of heroes, who fight against other players and their respective teams. Each player has a maximum of five characters (champions) of their own (or “creeps” as they are referred to). Each character starts with a basic skill (such as “Crowd Control” or “Magic Resist”) and a passive ability (such as Regeneration and Regeneration). Skill levels and passives are increased with experience points.

Once players reach level 10 (the “Summoner Level”), they can select a champion from a pool of over 30 champions. A champion can be changed at any time, provided they have enough experience points. Each champion has different strengths and weaknesses, and abilities that are unique to that champion.

LoL is played in two modes: “ ranked “and “unranked “. In ranked mode, players are divided into teams of 5 players. The highest ranked team wins. In unranked mode, every player is a champion, and the game is played by the individual players.

Who is the game for?

LoL is designed for players of any age and skill level. There are many different characters to choose from, and each one has their own strengths and weaknesses (some are better at team fights, others at magic damage, etc.). It is possible to play LoL with friends and family,
label: League of legends (LoL) is a multiplayer online battle game with a team of 5 players on each side of the arena playing against each other. Each player controls a "champion" with unique abilities and styles of the play. During the play, the champion of each player will become stronger by leveling up and collecting gold, which can be used to buy powerful items. The goal of the game is to destroy the "Nexus" of the opposite team.

The present invention relates to a process for producing a synthetic filament yarn with a good twist stiffness and good dimensional stability.
A known process for producing a synthetic filament yarn is that using an extruder and a forming-drawing-twisting yarn package. In the process, a thermoplastic resin, such as a polyester, is melted and extruded into molten yarn, which is then drawn into a yarn and formed by a package and further cooled. The yarn is wound on a package bobbin and is then thermally set to obtain a filament yarn.
The filament yarn thus obtained is very useful as a textile yarn. However, the filament yarn obtained by the known process has the following disadvantage: When a synthetic filament yarn is produced using a fiber spinning machine, for example, a spinning frame, a so-called "figure" is formed on a yarn. The figure is a twist irregularity in a yarn, which is caused by variations in the drawing conditions of the yarn. The figure gives a particular impression to the touch and causes a marked decrease in the quality of the yarn. Particularly, in a filament yarn, the twist irregularities are prominent and the figure is more conspicuous compared with a spun yarn.
As a process for removing the twist irregularity of a filament yarn, there has been proposed a process in which a filament yarn is twisted at a temperature higher than a temperature at which the yarn is thermally set to obtain a yarn with a twist stiffness higher than the thermal set twist stiffness. However, the twist stiffness of the yarn obtained in this process is extremely low. Further, in the process, the yarn obtained after twisting is twisted at a high temperature, and thus a thermal stress is applied to the yarn. Therefore, the yarn tends to be destroyed, and the yarn is not suitable for use as a textile yarn.
Further, a synthetic filament yarn is often formed into a fabric, and the yarn is then subjected to dyeing or finishing treatment. In the dyeing and finishing treatment, the yarn is subjected to a large tension and a large distortion. As a result, the yarn is damaged and the yarn is cut to have a yarn with a twist irregularity.

Why is the term "homeschooled" important?

Homeschooling is not the same as unschooling or unschooling. Homeschooling is not a choice, it's a requirement. Homeschooling is the legal and social process of teaching a child at home, usually through the use of a curriculum, textbooks, workbooks, etc. A person who homeschools is called a homeschooler. Keep in mind that states are free to assign the term "homeschool" to any school program that meets their state's requirements. Homeschooling is a legal requirement in all 50 states, and is also a requirement in the District of Columbia. For example, in the state of Oregon, homeschooling is defined as "the education of a child by a parent or other person with the child's consent, at the option of the parent or other person, in the child's own dwelling and under the direction of a person recognized by the State Board of Education as qualified to teach the subjects in the State-approved curriculum" (Oregon Revised Statute, Chapter 339).

Unschooling is a process of teaching children at home without the use of any curriculum or textbooks. In most homeschooling programs, some lessons may still be learned from books and worksheets, but unschooling is not the same as homeschooling. Unschooling is a choice, and unschooling is not a requirement. Neither is unschooling a requirement in every state.

Homeschooling is a requirement to be a member of many organizations, and unschooling is not a requirement to belong to any organizations. Many organizations, such as summer camps, Boy Scouts, Girls Scouts, 4-H, youth sports organizations,

There were various governing arrangements provided by the AoC, but the most important was protecting the power or sovereignty of the states.  The state would not have ratified the AoC if the federal government did not guarantee the powers of the states. The AoC defined a federal government with a unicameral legislature (one vote per state).  This legislation had the following powers: declare war, conduct “foreign or commercial relations with other countries” (i.e. treaties), and executive functions that would be carried out by legislative committees. It also “suggested a federal court system”.  This federal government was to be funded by the states.
Though it provided these powers to the federal government, there were inherent weaknesses built into the federal government. First, there was no way for the legislature to enforce its decisions. She graduated from the National Autonomous University of Mexico with a bachelor’s degree in International Relations and she later attended the Universidad Iberoamericana, where she earned a master’s degree in business administration.

In 2000, she married fellow lawyer Ernesto Arias, with whom she had three children. At the time of their marriage, Arias was a lawyer at the firm of Lozano, Hernández and Gómez, who represented major Mexican companies including Cemex.

In 2014, she appeared in the telenovela, El Señor de los Cielos, where she played the role of Liliana.

input: What is a Tommy John Surgery?
output:
oseh is a surgical operation that is commonly performed on a pitcher who has suffered a ligament tear in their ulnar collateral ligament (UCL), which is a ligament that runs from the ulnar aspect of the elbow to the ulnar side of the femur. A Tommy John Surgery is performed by a team of surgeons who have been specially trained as a result of their experience in repairing this ligament in major league pitchers. The procedure is named after Tommy John, the pitcher who in the early 1970s was the first to undergo it.

What is a Ulnar Collateral Ligament (UCL) Surgery?ulnar collateral ligament (UCL) is a type of ligament that connects the ulna and the radius of the forearm. Ligaments are fibrous bands that connect one bone to another. Ulnar collateral ligament (UCL) Injury is one of the most common elbow injuries in baseball, and it is usually caused by a pitch from a pitcher. Its name comes from Latin: ulna, "little bone", and collateral, "alongside".

How Does Tommy John Surgery Work?on Tommy John surgery, the ulnar nerve and its branches are rerouted through a tunnel created in the forearm. The ulnar nerve and its branches are then reattached to the ulnar side of the radius, which is the side of the forearm where the bone is located.

What is an Ulnar Collateral Ligament (UCL) Repair?ulnar collateral ligament (UCL) repair involves replacing the torn ligament with a graft. The ligament is taken from the same person who will eventually be the source of the graft, usually the patient's own ulnar collateral ligament. input: What is a quantum computer?
output:
oint.com/what-is-a-quantum-computer-3927.html

You can’t explain quantum computers using traditional methods of computation. They are fundamentally different. And they’ll never be faster than classical computers.

Jump to: navigation, search

Quantum computers will not be capable of solving any problem faster than classical computers. This is because they operate on binary bits.

Mathematically, this means that when a classical computer receives a data string, it will either be a 0 or a 1, and if it is a 1, then it will be that 1 forever. But in a quantum computer, the classical bits are constantly flipping between 0 and 1. The computer is constantly trying to measure the quantum bits, but in the end it can never measure them perfectly.

When you get a classical computer to solve a problem, you can tell it what the problem is, and it will take the correct answer. This is called the solution. On a quantum computer, the solution is unknown. It is not possible to know what the answer is.

Quantum computers will never be able to solve any new problem faster than classical computers.

But can quantum computers do anything well?

Quantum computers can do things that no classical computer can do. And they can do things that a classical computer could do, but would take a long, long time.

For example, a classical computer can do factoring. Factorization is a problem where you divide a number by a number, and you get a different number. For example, if you were trying to divide a number by 2, you would get 1, and if you were trying to divide 3, you would get 2. But a quantum computer can solve factoring by using “quantum error correction.” The error correction algorithm is a mathematical trick that allows the quantum computer to do something that no classical computer could do — to almost completely solve a number.

Quantum computers can simulate quantum systems. This means that they can model new quantum systems. For example, a quantum system would have a certain state, and then you can have a computer run the system. A classical computer could not do this, because if it tried to, it would never be able to find the final state of the system.

A quantum computer can also simulate quantum systems in a real way. This means that it can solve problems that a classical computer can’t. This is because a quantum computer is limited by its ability to solve the
label:
A quantum computer is a computer that exploits quantum mechanical phenomena. At small scales, physical matter exhibits properties of both particles and waves, and quantum computing leverages this behavior using specialized hardware. Classical physics cannot explain the operation of these quantum devices, and a scalable quantum computer could perform some calculations exponentially faster than any modern "classical" computer. In particular, a large-scale quantum computer could break widely used encryption schemes and aid physicists in performing physical simulations; however, the current state of the art is still largely experimental and impractical.

The basic unit of information in quantum computing is the qubit, similar to the bit in traditional digital electronics. Unlike a classical bit, a qubit can exist in a superposition of its two "basis" states, which loosely means that it is in both states simultaneously. When measuring a qubit, the result is a probabilistic output of a classical bit. If a quantum computer manipulates the qubit in a particular way, wave interference effects can amplify the desired measurement results. The design of quantum algorithms involves creating procedures that allow a quantum computer to perform calculations efficiently.

Physically engineering high-quality qubits has proven challenging. If a physical qubit is not sufficiently isolated from its environment, it suffers from quantum decoherence

output:
l

I am an admirer of Space Needle and I would like to know the height of it. I cannot visit Seattle very often now since the kids are at home. But I would like to know if I were to go back to Seattle, I can still get to the Space Needle. Please tell me how. I would also like to know the year it was built.

Space Needle is the tallest structure in Seattle. It was originally built for the 1962 World's Fair (Seattle World's Fair) and is located at the intersection of Fourth Avenue and Pike Street. It is also the tallest free-standing structure in the world.

The Space Needle was designed by the architects firm of Henry N. Cobb and Associates, and was constructed by the Seattle architectural firm of Graham and Anderson.

I really enjoy reading your posts and learn so much. I would like to know what is the best way to get to the Space Needle from downtown Seattle. Are there any shuttles that stop there?

The Space Needle is located in downtown Seattle on the Pike Street and Fourth Avenue corner.The Space Needle is not accessible by public transportation. You can either take a taxi (very expensive) or take the free "City Tour" bus, which stops at the Space Needle.

On the Space Needle web site you can print out a map of the city that includes the Space Needle.Look up the 'Seattle Worlds Fair' in the top left-hand corner of the map. The Space Needle is the tallest structure. It is built on a steel framework that allows it to move up and down as needed.

I would like to know the height of the Space Needle in feet, inches and length. Also, if there is a way to get to the top of the Space Needle without taking the elevator. Is there a ramp on the side of the building? If so, how high is the top of the Space Needle?

No, there is not a ramp on the side of the Space Needle. There are two elevators on each side of the Space Needle. The elevators go to the top of the Space Needle (the observation deck). The observation deck is the highest public observation deck in the world.

The Space Needle is an observation tower that was built for the 1962 World's Fair in Seattle. It is the tallest structure in Seattle.

label: The Space Needle was built in 1962 and it is located in Lower Queen Anne area in the city of Seattle. The tower has a height of 605 feet and it takes 41 seconds for visitors to reach the top of it with an elevator.

The present invention relates to a semiconductor device including an interposer for interconnecting a plurality of semiconductor chips, and to a multi-chip module (MCM) including the semiconductor device.
A semiconductor chip is mounted on a circuit substrate such as a printed circuit board, and the circuit substrate is connected to a motherboard for example. The mounting of the semiconductor chip on the circuit substrate is called face-down mounting. To mount the semiconductor chip on the circuit substrate in the face-down mounting, it is necessary to electrically connect terminals of the semiconductor chip to terminals of the circuit substrate. For this purpose, an interposer is used.
In the face-down mounting, a plurality of semiconductor chips are mounted on the same circuit substrate. In this case, the plurality of semiconductor chips have the same shape as the semiconductor chip mounted on the circuit substrate. Therefore, a plurality of semiconductor chips on the same circuit substrate are referred to as a multi-chip module (MCM).
The printed circuit board is connected to the motherboard by connectors. Examples of the connectors include a SIL connector, a QFP connector and a PGA connector. The SIL connector, the QFP connector and the PGA connector are formed by stacking

Boston is a very historical city in the context of the development and history of the United State.  Boston is the capital and largest city of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts and the cultural and financial center of the New England region of the Northeastern United States. The city boundaries encompass an area of about 48.4 sq mi (125 km2) and a population of 675,647 as of 2020. The city is the economic and cultural anchor of a substantially larger metropolitan area known as Greater Boston, a metropolitan statistical area (MSA) home to a census-estimated 4.8 million people in 2016 and ranking as the tenth-largest MSA in the country. 

Boston is one of the oldest municipalities in America, founded on the Shawmut Peninsula in 1630 by Puritan settlers from the English town of the same name. It was the scene of several key events of the American Revolution and the nation's founding, such as the Boston Massacre, the Boston Tea Party, the Battle of Bunker Hill, and the siege of Boston. Upon American independence from Great Britain, the city continued to be an important port and manufacturing hub as well as a center for education and culture.
